sheAdslMib.name: sheAdslMib

revisions.description: Take over by Gerd Barchmann for R2.5. Merge on base she MIB version 151.
Delete entrys from extnProfileControl-group for elements which could not be modified. Same for extnProfileModified-notification. Move AdslLineAlarm's to separate group (like in vshe).

Add support for dualLatency. Needed changes made for access channeltable's and new parameter in vcctp-table. SHE releases smaller then R2.5 will support old channel tables without channeltype index (NO dualLatency support)! SHE release R2.5 and higher support new channel tables with additional channeltype index (dualLatency supported)! Add some removed elements for backward compatibility of the managment system. The NE release up R2.5 will still NOT support this elements!
New merge with SHE R2.3 MIB-Version 153. Expand value list for SheAdslLineConfUpstreamPSDMaskSelectionType.

Minor corrections for backward compatibility. OID changes for sheAdslAtuc-Notifications (also backward compatibility). Modify description for usedDslChannel in VccTp-Table. Modify description for linetype configuration.
Minor corrections for backward compatibility. Correct default value for VccTp-UsedChannel.
Merge with SHE R2.3 MIB release 156.
Expand range for SheAdslConfMinInpType.

New for R2.5.2. Add sheAdslLineDpboProfileTable. Assignment via sheAdslLineTable. Add separate INP configuration value for US direction to extn. Profile. Add sheAdslVccTpPerformanceCounter - Table. Add sheAdslVccTpEncapType to sheAdslVccTpTable.
Add enum value for support adsl2adsl2PlusOnly standard via sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileStandard value. Add modified trap for DpboProfile assignment.
Correct type for VccTpAlarmSeverityIndex.
Correct only descripions regarding feature support in version SHE R2.6.
Correct setting for sheAdslLineControlRfiBandMask.

sheAdslLineDpboProfileMof not longer supported. Correct description for MinINP=0. Merge MIB release 160 from SHE R2.3 -> support for SES and UAS ThresholdAlarms. Merge MIB release for SHE R2.4 -> sheAdslLineInpValueTruncatedInto2 added into sheAdslConfigurationTraps and add sheAdslAtucPhysCurrentBinStatus.
Expand AtucPhys and AturPhys table with BinBitLoading parameters.
Modify sheAdslLineInpValueTruncatedInto2 object list (requested by Zhao Ran).
Support additional parameters for DELT status in AtuxPhysTable with SHE R2.4. Correct syntax for SheAdslLineConfNtrType. Add parameter to AdslLineAlarmConfModifiedTrap.
Correct description of minInp value 0 -> null!
Add detailed failure returncode definitions to ReqResult enum. The scheduled support release is not defined yet.

Add support for a dynamic use of annex types A/B/I/J by a single adsl line profile. Support will start with SHE R2.8. This causes some restrictions to extn. profile parameter settings. A new specific profile create command was defined.
Add missing value for AdvertisedCapability definition.

sheAdslMib.description: The MIB module to describe ADSL product. The MIB module that provides objects that are proprietary and extension to ADSL- LINE-MIB.The MIB includes the following Tables. 1.) adslLineTable 2.) adslAtucPhysTable 3.) adslAturPhysTable 4.) adslAtucChanTable 5.) adslAturChanTable 6.) adslAtucPerfDataTable 7.) adslAtucIntervalTable 8.) adslAtucChanPerfDataTable 9.) adslAturChanPerfDataTable 10.) adslAtucChanIntervalTable 11.) adslAturChanIntervalTable 12.) adslLineConfProfileTable 13.) adslLineConfExtnProfileTable 13.) adslLineAlarmConfProfileTable 14.) adslVccTpTable 15.) adslRfiMaskTable

sheAdslCapabilityLineTxCap.description: This bitmap specifies all transmission modes, which the ATU-C is capable of supporting. Right now support for Annex A (q9921PotsNonOverlapped(2) and q9921PotsOverlapped(3)) is present. This value depends on the DSL PHY firmware present on Columbia MND unused(0), etsi(1), q9921PotsNonOverlapped(2), q9921PotsOverlapped(3), q9921IsdnNonOverlapped(4), q9921IsdnOverlapped(5), q9921TcmIsdnNonOverlapped(6), q9921TcmIsdnOverlapped(7), q9922PotsNonOverlapped(8), q9922PotsOverlapped(9), q9922TcmIsdnNonOverlapped(10), q9922TcmIsdnOverlapped(11), q9922TcmIsdnSymmetric(12), adslPlusPotsNonOverlapped(13)

sheAdslLineConfProfileTable.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileTable
sheAdslLineConfProfileTable.description: This table contains information on the ADSL line configuration. One entry in this table reflects a profile defined by a manager which can be used to configure the ADSL line.

sheAdslLineConfProfileEntry.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileEntry
sheAdslLineConfProfileEntry.description: Each entry consists of a list of parameters that represents the configuration of an ADSL modem. `Dynamic' profiles are implemented. A default profile will always exist. This profile's name will be set to `DEFVAL' and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

sheAdslLineConfProfileName.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileName
sheAdslLineConfProfileName.description: This object is used by the line configuration table in order to identify a row of this table. Dynamic profiles are implemented. The profile name is user specified. Also, the system will always provide a default profile whose name is `DEFVAL' for Annex A and DEFVAL_ISDN fpr Annex B card's (both Adsl2+). Special characters are not allowed, like: space : ?

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfRateMode.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfRateMode
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfRateMode.description: Defines what form of transmit rate adaptation is configured on this modem. See ADSL Forum TR-005 [3] for more information. fixed(1), adaptAtStartup(2), adaptAtRuntime(3)

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfRateChanRa.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfRateChanRatio
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfRateChanRa.description: Configured allocation ratio of excess transmit bandwidth between fast and interleaved channels. Only applies when two channel mode and rate adaptive DSL are supported. A ratio of 20% means, that 20 % of the available data rate (in access of the minimum rate summend over all bearer channels) will be assigned to the fast channel and 80% to the interleaved channel. Only valid if sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileLineType is set to dualLatency mode.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfTargetSnrM.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfTargetSnrMgn
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfTargetSnrM.description: Configured Target Signal/Noise Margin. This is the Noise Margin the modem must achieve with a BER of 10-7 or better to successfully complete initialization.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMaxSnrMgn.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMaxSnrMgn
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMaxSnrMgn.description: Configured Maximum acceptable Signal/Noise Margin. If the Noise Margin is above this the modem should attempt to reduce its power output to optimize its operation.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMinSnrMgn.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMinSnrMgn
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMinSnrMgn.description: Configured Minimum acceptable Signal/Noise Margin. If the noise margin falls below this level, the modem should attempt to increase its power output. If that is not possible the modem will attempt to re-initialize or shut down.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfDownshiftS.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfDownshiftSnrMgn
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfDownshiftS.description: Configured Signal/Noise Margin for rate downshift. If the noise margin falls below this level, the modem should attempt to decrease its transmit rate. In the case that adaptAtRuntime mode is not present, the value will be 'don't care'.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfUpshiftSnr.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfUpshiftSnrMgn
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfUpshiftSnr.description: Configured Signal/Noise Margin for rate upshift. If the noise margin rises above this level, the modem should attempt to increase its transmit rate. In the case that adaptAtRuntime mode is not present, the value will be 'don't care'.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMinUpshift.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMinUpshiftTime
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMinUpshift.description: Minimum time that the current margin is above UpshiftSnrMgn before an upshift occurs. In the case that adaptAtRuntime mode is not present, the value will be 'don't care'.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMinDownshi.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMinDownshiftTime
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfMinDownshi.description: Minimum time that the current margin is below DownshiftSnrMgn before a downshift occurs. In the case that adaptAtRuntime mode is not present, the value will be 'don't care'.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfFastMi.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfFastMinTxRate
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfFastMi.description: Configured Minimum Transmit rate for `Fast' channels, in kbps. See adslAtucConfRateChanRatio for information regarding RADSL mode and ATUR transmit rate for ATUC receive rates. Only multiples of 32 will be configured.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfInterl.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfInterleaveMinTxRate
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfInterl.description: Configured Minimum Transmit rate for `Interleave' channels, in kbps. See adslAtucConfRateChanRatio for information regarding RADSL mode and see ATUR transmit rate for receive rates. Only multiples of 32 will be configured.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfFastMa.description: Configured Maximum Transmit rate for `Fast' channels, in kbps. See adslAtucConfRateChanRatio for information regarding RADSL mode and see ATUR transmit rate for ATUC receive rates. Only multiples of 32 will be configured.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfInterl.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfInterleaveMaxTxRate

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfMaxInt.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfMaxInterleaveDelay
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfMaxInt.description: Configured maximum Interleave Delay for this channel. Interleave delay applies only to the interleave channel and defines the mapping (relative spacing) between subsequent input bytes at the interleaver input and their placement in the bit stream at the interleaver output. Larger numbers provide greater separation between consecutive input bytes in the output bit stream allowing for improved impulse noise immunity at the expense of payload latency.

sheAdslLineConfProfileTrellis.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileTrellis
sheAdslLineConfProfileTrellis.description: Indicates if Trelliscoding is enabled or not. If TrellisCoding is used is indicated in sheAdslLineTable and depence also on the Atur-Capabilities. The NE will not accept setting trellisOff. It is automatically controlled by firmware and will be switched off if ATU-R will not support this.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL0T.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL0Time
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL0T.description: This parameter represents the minimum time (in seconds) between an exit from the L2 state and the next entry into the L2 state. It ranges from 0 to 255 seconds. Only valid for Adsl2 and Adsl2Plus.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL2T.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL2Time
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL2T.description: This parameter represents the minimum time (in seconds) between an Entry into the L2 state and the first Power Trim in the L2 state and between two consecutive Power Trims in the L2 State. It ranges from 0 to 255 seconds. Only valid for Adsl2 and Adsl2Plus.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL2A.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL2ATPR
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL2A.description: This parameter represents the maximum aggregate transmit power reduction (in dB) that can be performed through a single Power Trim in the L2 state. It ranges from 0 dB/10 to 310 dB/10. Only valid for Adsl2 and Adsl2Plus.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL2R.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL2Rate
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtL2R.description: This parameter specifies the minimum net data rate during the low power state (L2). The data rate is coded in bit/s, and can range from 0x1F40 (8000) bps to 0xFA000 (1024000) bps. Only valid for Adsl2 and Adsl2Plus.

sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtMod.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtMode
sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfPwrMgmtMod.description: Which ADSL Power Management state is enabled. Only valid for Adsl2 and Adsl2Plus.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfTar.description: Configured Target Signal/Noise Margin. This is the Noise Margin the modem must achieve with a BER of 10-7 or better to successfully complete initialization.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMax.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMaxSnrMgn
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMax.description: Configured Maximum acceptable Signal/Noise Margin. If the Noise Margin is above this the modem should attempt to reduce its power output to optimize its operation.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMin.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMinSnrMgn
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMin.description: Configured Minimum acceptable Signal/Noise Margin. If the noise margin falls below this level, the modem should attempt to increase its power output. If that is not possible the modem will attempt to re-initialize or shut down.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfDow.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfDownshiftSnrMgn
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfDow.description: Configured Signal/Noise Margin for rate downshift. If the noise margin falls below this level, the modem should attempt to decrease its transmit rate. In the case that RADSL mode is not present, the value will be `0'.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfUps.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfUpshiftSnrMgn
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfUps.description: Configured Signal/Noise Margin for rate upshift. If the noise margin rises above this level, the modem should attempt to increase its transmit rate. In the case that RADSL is not present, the value will be `0'.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMin.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMinUpshiftTime
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMin.description: Minimum time that the current margin is above UpshiftSnrMgn before an upshift occurs. In the case that RADSL is not present, the value will be `0'.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMin.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMinDownshiftTime
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturConfMin.description: Minimum time that the current margin is below DownshiftSnrMgn before a downshift occurs. In the case that RADSL mode is not present, the value will be `0'.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanCon.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanConfFastMinTxRate
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanCon.description: Configured Minimum Transmit rate for `Fast' channels, in kbps. See adslAturConfRateChanRatio for information regarding RADSL mode and ATUC transmit rate for ATUR receive rates. Only multiples of 32 will be configured.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanCon.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanConfInterleaveMinTxRate
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanCon.description: Configured Minimum Transmit rate for `Interleave' channels, in kbps. See adslAturConfRateChanRatio for information regarding RADSL mode and ATUC transmit rate for ATUR receive rates. Only multiples of 32 will be configured.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanCon.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanConfFastMaxTxRate
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanCon.description: Configured Maximum Transmit rate for `Fast' channels, in kbps. See adslAturConfRateChanRatio for information regarding RADSL mode and ATUC transmit rate for ATUR receive rates. Only multiples of 32 will be configured.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanCon.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanConfInterleaveMaxTxRate
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanCon.description: Configured Maximum Transmit rate for `Interleave' channels, in kbps. See adslAturConfRateChanRatio for information regarding RADSL mode and see ATUC transmit rate for ATUR receive rates. Only multiples of 32 will be configured.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanCon.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanConfMaxInterleaveDelay
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAturChanCon.description: Configured maximum Interleave Delay for this channel. Interleave delay applies only to the interleave channel and defines the mapping (relative spacing) between subsequent input bytes at the interleaver input and their placement in the bit stream at the interleaver output. Larger numbers provide greater separation between consecutive input bytes in the output bit stream allowing for improved impulse noise immunity at the expense of payload latency.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlTrellis.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlTrellis
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlTrellis.description: Indicates if Trelliscoding is enabled or not. If TrellisCoding is used is indicated in sheAdslLineTable and depence also on the Atur-Capabilities. Do not touch!

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwr.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwrMgmtL0Time
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwr.description: This parameter represents the minimum time (in seconds) between an exit from the L2 state and the next entry into the L2 state. It ranges from 0 to 255 seconds. Only valid for Adsl2 and Adsl2Plus.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwr.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwrMgmtL2Time
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwr.description: This parameter represents the minimum time (in seconds) between an Entry into the L2 state and the first Power Trim in the L2 state and between two consecutive Power Trims in the L2 State. It ranges from 0 to 255 seconds. Only valid for Adsl2 and Adsl2Plus.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwr.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwrMgmtL2ATPR
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwr.description: This parameter represents the maximum aggregate transmit power reduction (in dB) that can be performed through a single Power Trim in the L2 state. It ranges from 0 dB/10 to 310 dB/10. Only valid for Adsl2 and Adsl2Plus.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwr.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwrMgmtL2Rate
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwr.description: This parameter specifies the minimum net data rate during the low power state (L2). The data rate is coded in bit/s, and can range from 0x1F40 (8000) bps to 0xFA000 (1024000) bps. Only valid for Adsl2 and Adsl2Plus.

sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwr.name: sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwrMgmtMode
sheAdslLineConfProfileControlAtucConfPwr.description: Which ADSL Power Management state is enabled. Only valid for Adsl2 and Adsl2Plus.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTable.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTable
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTable.description: This table contains information on the ADSL line configuration. One entry in this table reflects a profile defined by a manager which can be used to configure the ADSL line.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileEntry.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileEntry
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileEntry.description: Each entry consists of a list of parameters that represents the configuration of an ADSL modem. The index is used from the sheAdslLineConfProfileTable.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileParametricTest.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileParametricTestInputFile
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileParametricTest.description: Indicates Name of the Input file from which to take the Mask Array Size, lower and upper mask Array. Null string means no file is specified. Functionality is not supported!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsIntCorrectio.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsIntCorrectionUp
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsIntCorrectio.description: Sets the correction time for the upstream-interleaved buffer. RS can also be disabled. The Default Value for ADSL+ is 3. value125us(3), value250us(4), value500us(5), value1ms(6), value2ms(7), value4ms(8), disable(15)

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileLineType.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileLineType
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileLineType.description: This parameter provisions the DSL physical entity at start-up by defining whether and how the line will be channelized, i.e. which channel type(s) are supported. Defined values are: fastOnly(2) -- only fast channel exists (singleLatency) interleavedOnly(3) -- only interleaved channel exists (singleLatency, default) fastAndInterleaved(5) -- both fast and interleaved channels (dualLatency) exist In case of dualLatency (mode 5), the parameter's sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfRateChanRatio and sheAdslLineConfProfileAturConfRateChanRatio configures the bandwith distribution. IMPORTANT NOTE: The configuration of dualLatency mode is only available for NE releases up R2.5!! The modification is only possible for profiles, which are NOT IN USE!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTxEndBin.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTxEndBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTxEndBin.description: Highest bin number allowed for Tx signal. The Range & default for ADSL+ is 0x06 - 0x1ff respectively. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value! Ne will select the correct values depending on the configuration of the following values: - AnnexType - DmtConfMode - AdvertisedCapability New with R2.8: If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', no values of Tx/Rx bins could be set here, because this will be done by the IU depending on the used HW and choosen standard. The profile configuration will be set to value 65535 (0xffff) which means 'autoSelect'.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTxStartBin.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTxStartBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTxStartBin.description: Lowest bin number allowed for Tx signal.The Range for ADSL+ is 0x06 - 0x1ff. The Default for Annex B is 58 respectively. For AnnexA it is 32. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value! Ne will select the correct values depending on the configuration of the following values: - AnnexType - DmtConfMode - AdvertisedCapability New with R2.8: If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', no values of Tx/Rx bins could be set here, because this will be done by the IU depending on the used HW and choosen standard. The profile configuration will be set to value 65535 (0xffff) which means 'autoSelect'.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxBitsPerBin.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxBitsPerBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxBitsPerBin.description: Maximum Rx number of bits per bin. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRxStartBin.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRxStartBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRxStartBin.description: Lowest bin number allowed for Rx signal. Default value for AnnexA is 6 and 32 for AnnexB. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value! Ne will select the correct values depending on the configuration of the following values: - AnnexType - DmtConfMode - AdvertisedCapability New with R2.8: If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', no values of Tx/Rx bins could be set here, because this will be done by the IU depending on the used HW and choosen standard. The profile configuration will be set to value 65535 (0xffff) which means 'autoSelect'.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRxEndBin.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRxEndBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRxEndBin.description: Highest bin number allowed for Rx signal. Default Value for AnnexA is 31 and 57 for AnnexB. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value! Ne will select the correct values depending on the configuration of the following values: - AnnexType - DmtConfMode - AdvertisedCapability New with R2.8: If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', no values of Tx/Rx bins could be set here, because this will be done by the IU depending on the used HW and choosen standard. The profile configuration will be set to value 65535 (0xffff) which means 'autoSelect'.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRxBinAdjust.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRxBinAdjust
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRxBinAdjust.description: Employs Rx Start/End bin settings. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTriggerMode.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTriggerMode
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTriggerMode.description: Indicates the Type of event that triggers fast retrain. disable(0), locCrc(1), rmtCrc(2), snrInc(4), snrDec(8) NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAdi2x.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAdi2x
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAdi2x.description: For non standard compliant ADI CPE. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileStandard.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileStandard
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileStandard.description: Preferred standard compliance. Outcome is dependent upon standard support of the remote unit.GlobespanVirata High Speed ADSL DMT (ADSL+) applications only. t1413(0), gLite(1), gDmt(2), multiMode(4), adsl2(26), adsl2_plus(27), readsl2(28), adsl2_auto(29), adsl2_plus_auto(30), adsl2adsl2PlusOnly(31) New with R2.8: If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', the standardTypes 't1413', 'gLite', 'gDmt' and 'readsl2' could NOT be used. 'adsl2_plus_auto' should be the prefered use in that case!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileInitiate.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileInitiate
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileInitiate.description: Specifies which end initiates startup. It is also used to send a C-tone to the remote unit. waitPn(0), ctone(1), initiatePn(128) NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTxPowerAttenua.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTxPowerAttenuation
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileTxPowerAttenua.description: Specifies value of Tx power attenuation. value0(0)...value21(21)

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileCodingGain.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileCodingGain
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileCodingGain.description: Sets the coding gain in dB increments. gain0(0), gain1(4096), gain2(8192), gain3(12288), gain4(16384), gain5(20480), gain6(24576), gain7(28672), auto(65280) NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsFastOvrhdDow.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsFastOvrhdDown
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsFastOvrhdDow.description: Sets the percentage overhead for the downstream-fast buffer. ovrHd50(1), ovrHd25(2), ovrHd12(3), ovrHd6(4), ovrHd3(5), ovrHd1(7), disable(15) NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileIntCorrectionD.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileIntCorrectionDown
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileIntCorrectionD.description: This parameter sets the correction time for the downstream interleaved buffer. RS can also be disabled. value125us(3), value250us(4), value500us(5), value1ms(6), value2ms(7), value4ms(8), disable(15)

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsFastOvrhdUp.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsFastOvrhdUp
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsFastOvrhdUp.description: Sets the percentage overhead for the upstream-fast buffer. ovrHd50(1), ovrHd25(2), ovrHd12(3), ovrHd6(4), ovrHd3(5), ovrHd1(7), disable(15) NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileDrStby.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileDrStby
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileDrStby.description: Provides the ability to disable power to the line driver. disable(0), enable(1) NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileExpandedExchan.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileExpandedExchange
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileExpandedExchan.description: This object is used to Enable/Disable EES. disable(0), enable(1) NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileEscapeFastRetr.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileEscapeFastRetrainEnable
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileEscapeFastRetr.description: This object is used to Enable/ Disable escape to the fast retrain capability. disable(0), enable(1) NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileFastRetrainEna.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileFastRetrainEnable
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileFastRetrainEna.description: This object is used to Enable/ Disable the fast retrain capability. disable(32768), enable(0) NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileBitSwap.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileBitSwap
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileBitSwap.description: This object is used to Enable/Disable bit swapping. enable(32768), disable(0)

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileNtr.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileNtr
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileNtr.description: This object is used to Enable/ Disable NTR on a per chip basis.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAnnexType.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAnnexType
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAnnexType.description: This parameter is set as per annex compliance of the code release. GlobespanVirata High Speed ADSL DMT (ADSL+) applications only. annexA(0), annexB(1), highSpeed(2), annexAdsl2(5), annexI(10), annexJ(11), annexM(12) New with R2.8: dynamic(50) If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', such a profile could be assigned to any type of supported ADSL IU. The IU will select the supported annex himself, depending on HW restrictions and line parameters. This selection made additional restrictions to the following parameters: - tx/rx start and end bin usage - profile Standard - profile AdvertisedCapabilities - profileLineDmtConfMode

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAlctlUsVer.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAlctlUsVer
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAlctlUsVer.description: This object is used for T1.413 demo purposes only. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileUseCustomBin.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileUseCustomBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileUseCustomBin.description: This object is used to Enable/ Disable user selection of bin-usage defined in sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileDnBinUsage. disable(0), enable(32768)

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileDnBinUsage.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileDnBinUsage
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileDnBinUsage.description: The parameter where a 1 in bit position indicates usage of corresponding bin, whereas a 0 disables usage of corresponding bin.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxDCo.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxDCo
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxDCo.description: This object is used to indicate Maximum interleaving depth supported by the customer's hardware. value64(0), value128(4096), value256(8192)

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileFullRetrain.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileFullRetrain
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileFullRetrain.description: This object is used to Indicate enable/disable of auto retrain capability. enable(0), disable(32768) NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAdvertisedCapa.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAdvertisedCapabilities
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileAdvertisedCapa.description: Controls if the CO will attempt to startup using alternate standards if the CPE does not support ADSL+. New with R2.8: If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', this parameter should be set to 'disabled' or 'adslPlus'. All other values will not work with the intended set of dynamic annexType selection by IU.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfilePsdMaskType.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfilePsdMaskType
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfilePsdMaskType.description: Selects the PSD mask option to be used.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileLineDmtConfMod.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileLineDmtConfMode
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileLineDmtConfMod.description: Selects if there is overlap or no overlap of bins. Overlapping is only supported by non ISDN profiles and will change the setting for TxStartBin accordingly!!. New with R2.8: If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', this parameter should be set to 'fdmMode' only. Other values will not work with the intended set of dynamic annexType selection by IU.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileEraseProfiles.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileEraseProfiles
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileEraseProfiles.description: Enables/Disables the ability to erase all fast retrain profiles at startup. disable(0), enable(32768)

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsMemory.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsMemory
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRsMemory.description: Indicates whether customer's Hardware should use external RS RAM. Could not be configured and depends only on the used card type.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileParamHybridLos.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileParamHybridLossTestStart
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileParamHybridLos.description: Indicates Start bin for range of bins to be measured.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileParamHybridLos.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileParamHybridLossTestEnd
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileParamHybridLos.description: Indicates End bin for range of bins to be measured.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileConfMinInp.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileConfMinInp
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileConfMinInp.description: New ADSL2+ parameter. The user configures the duration of impulse noise the system should withstand. This parameter configures the value for downstream direction.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRfiBandMask.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRfiBandMask
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileRfiBandMask.description: BitMask for sheAdslRfiBandIndex. Configured RFI bands are used for this profile.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileUpstreamPsdMas.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileUpstreamPsdMaskSelection
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileUpstreamPsdMas.description: Selects the PSD mask option to be used. This parameter is used only for annexes J and M of ITU-T Recs. G.992-3 and G.992.5 Other profiles will ignore the configured value and use per default the value noSelection(0).

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxNomPsdDs.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxNomPsdDs
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxNomPsdDs.description: The maximum nominal transmit PSD in the downstream direction during initialization and Showtime. It ranges from -600 to -300 units of 0.1 dBm/Hz. (physical values are -60 to -30 dBm/Hz).

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxNomAtpDs.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxNomAtpDs
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileMaxNomAtpDs.description: The maximum nominal aggregate transmit power in the downstream direction during initialization and Showtime. It ranges from 0 to 255 units of 0.1 dBm (physical values are 0 to 25.5 dBm).

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfilePsdMaskDs.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfilePsdMaskDs
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfilePsdMaskDs.description: The downstream PSD mask applicable at the U-C2 reference point. This parameter is used only for G.992.5 and it may impose PSD restrictions (breakpoints) in addition to the Limit PSD mask defined in G.992.5. This is a string of 32 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1. Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint. Octets 6-8 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint. This architecture continues until octets 94-95, which are associated with a 32nd breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 1 and NSCds. Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). But the range of start-bin and end-bin is in range 0 to 195 (0 to -97.5dBm/Hz). Two break points (6 byte) are reserved for start sub-carrier index and end sub-carrier index. So the range of size is 6 up to 96. When the number of breakpoints is less than 32, all remaining octets are set to the value 0. Note that the content of this object should be correlated with the sub-carriers mask and with the RFI setup.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfilePSDMASKdsEnabl.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfilePSDMASKdsEnable
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfilePSDMASKdsEnabl.description: User custom PSD mask-related parameter used by the ATU-C to use user custom PSD mask. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 and ADSL2plus ).

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileConfMinInpUs.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileConfMinInpUs
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileConfMinInpUs.description: New ADSL2+ parameter. The user configures the duration of impulse noise the system should withstand. This parameter configures the value for upstream direction.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlIndex.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlIndex
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlIndex.description: Index of the table entry to be configured. Needed for modify.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlStatus.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlStatus
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTimer.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTimer
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlReqResu.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlReqResult
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlReqResu.description: The result of the last user command.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTimeSta.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTimeStamp
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTimeSta.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlName.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlName
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlName.description: Descriptional name. The name used during configuration of this profile is equal to the name of the sheAdslLineConfProfile with the identical index.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlParamet.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlParametricTestInputFile
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlParamet.description: Indicates Name of the Input file from which to take the Mask Array Size, lower and upper mask Array. Null string means no file is specified.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRsIntCo.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRsIntCorrectionUp
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRsIntCo.description: Sets the correction time for the upstream-interleaved buffer. RS can also be disabled. The Default Value for ADSL+ is 3.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlLineTyp.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlLineType
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlLineTyp.description: This parameter provisions the DSL physical entity at start-up by defining whether and how the line will be channelized, i.e. which channel type(s) are supported. Defined values are: fastOnly(2) -- only fast channel exists (singleLatency) interleavedOnly(3) -- only interleaved channel exists (singleLatency, default) fastAndInterleaved(5) -- both fast and interleaved channels (dualLatency) exist In case of dualLatency (mode 5), the parameter's sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfRateChanRatio and sheAdslLineConfProfileAturConfRateChanRatio configures the bandwith distribution. IMPORTANT NOTE: The configuration of dualLatency mode is only available for NE releases up R2.5!! The modification is only possible for profiles, which are NOT IN USE!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTxEndBi.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTxEndBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTxEndBi.description: Highest bin number allowed for Tx signal. The Range & default for ADSL+ is 0x06 - 0x1ff respectively. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value! Ne will select the correct values depending on the configuration of the following values: - AnnexType - DmtConfMode - AdvertisedCapability

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTxStart.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTxStartBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTxStart.description: Lowest bin number allowed for Tx signal.The Range for ADSL+ is 0x06 - 0x1ff. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value! Ne will select the correct values depending on the configuration of the following values: - AnnexType - DmtConfMode - AdvertisedCapability

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxBits.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxBitsPerBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxBits.description: Maximum Rx number of bits per bin. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRxStart.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRxStartBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRxStart.description: Lowest bin number allowed for Rx signal. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value! Ne will select the correct values depending on the configuration of the following values: - AnnexType - DmtConfMode - AdvertisedCapability

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRxEndBi.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRxEndBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRxEndBi.description: Highest bin number allowed for Rx signal. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value! Ne will select the correct values depending on the configuration of the following values: - AnnexType - DmtConfMode - AdvertisedCapability

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRxBinAd.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRxBinAdjust
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRxBinAd.description: Employs Rx Start/End bin settings. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTrigger.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTriggerMode
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTrigger.description: Indicates the Type of event that triggers fast retrain. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAdi2x.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAdi2x
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAdi2x.description: For non standard compliant ADI CPE. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlStandar.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlStandard
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlStandar.description: Preferred standard compliance. Outcome is dependent upon standard support of the remote unit.GlobespanVirata High Speed ADSL DMT (ADSL+) applications only. New with R2.8: If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', the standardTypes 't1413', 'gLite', 'gDmt' and 'readsl2' could NOT be used. 'adsl2_plus_auto' should be the prefered use in that case!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlInitiat.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlInitiate
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlInitiat.description: Specifies which end initiates startup. It is also used to send a C-tone to the remote unit. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTxPower.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTxPowerAttenuation
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlTxPower.description: Specifies value of Tx power attenuation.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlCodingG.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlCodingGain
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlCodingG.description: Sets the coding gain in dB increments. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRsFastO.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRsFastOvrhdDown
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRsFastO.description: Sets the percentage overhead for the downstream-fast buffer. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlIntCorr.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlIntCorrectionDown
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlIntCorr.description: This parameter sets the correction time for the downstream interleaved buffer.RS can also be disabled.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRsFastO.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRsFastOvrhdUp
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlRsFastO.description: Sets the percentage overhead for the upstream-fast buffer. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlDrStby.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlDrStby
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlDrStby.description: Provides the ability to disable power to the line driver. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlExpande.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlExpandedExchange
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlExpande.description: This object is used to Enable/Disable EES. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlEscapeF.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlEscapeFastRetrainEnable
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlEscapeF.description: This object is used to Enable/ Disable escape to the fast retrain capability. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlFastRet.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlFastRetrainEnable
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlFastRet.description: This object is used to Enable/ Disable the fast retrain capability. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlBitSwap.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlBitSwap
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlBitSwap.description: This object is used to Enable/Disable bit swapping.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlNtr.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlNtr
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlNtr.description: This object is used to Enable/ Disable NTR on a per chip basis.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAnnexTy.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAnnexType
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAnnexTy.description: This parameter is set as per annex compliance of the code release. GlobespanVirata High Speed ADSL DMT (ADSL+) applications only. New with R2.8: dynamic(50) If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', such a profile could be assigned to any type of supported ADSL IU. The IU will select the supported annex himself, depending on HW restrictions and line parameters. This selection made additional restrictions to the following parameters: - tx/rx start and end bin usage - profile Standard - profile AdvertisedCapabilities - profileLineDmtConfMode

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAlctlUs.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAlctlUsVer
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAlctlUs.description: This object is used for T1.413 demo purposes only. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlUseCust.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlUseCustomBin
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlUseCust.description: This object is used to Enable/ Disable user selection on which of the 256 bins will be enabled for downstream transmission.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlDnBinUs.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlDnBinUsage
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlDnBinUs.description: The parameter where a 1 in bit position indicates usage of corresponding bin,whereas a 0 disables usage of corresponding bin.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxDCo.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxDCo
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxDCo.description: This object is used to indicate Maximum interleaving depth supported by the customer's hardware.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlFullRet.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlFullRetrain
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlFullRet.description: This object is used to Indicate enable/disable of auto retrain capability. NE will not accept any changes and use always default value!

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAdverti.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAdvertisedCapabilities
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlAdverti.description: Controls if the CO will attempt to startup using alternate standards if the CPE does not support ADSL+. New with R2.8: If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', this parameter should be set to 'disabled' or 'adslPlus'. All other values will not work with the intended set of dynamic annexType selection by IU.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPsdMask.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPsdMaskType
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPsdMask.description: Selects the PSD mask option to be used.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlLineDmt.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlLineDmtConfMode
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlLineDmt.description: Selects if there is overlap or no overlap of bins. Overlapping is only supported by non ISDN profiles and will change the setting for TxStartBin accordingly!!. New with R2.8: If the used annexType was set to 'dynamic', this parameter should be set to 'fdmMode' only. Other values will not work with the intended set of dynamic annexType selection by IU.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlErasePr.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlEraseProfiles
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlErasePr.description: Enables/Disables the ability to erase all fast retrain profiles at startup.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlParamHy.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlParamHybridLossTestStart
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlParamHy.description: Indicates Start bin for range of bins to be measured.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlParamHy.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlParamHybridLossTestEnd
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlParamHy.description: Indicates End bin for range of bins to be measured.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlUpstrea.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlUpstreamPsdMaskSelection
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlUpstrea.description: This configuration parameter defines which upstream PSD mask is enabled. This parameter is used only for annexes J and M of ITU-T Recs. G.992-3 and G.992.5

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxNomP.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxNomPsdDs
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxNomP.description: The maximum nominal transmit PSD in the downstream direction during initialization and Showtime. It ranges from -600 to -300 units of 0.1 dBm/Hz. (physical values are -60 to -30 dBm/Hz).

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxNomA.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxNomAtpDs
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlMaxNomA.description: The maximum nominal aggregate transmit power in the downstream direction during initialization and Showtime. It ranges from 0 to 255 units of 0.1 dBm (physical values are 0 to 25.5 dBm).

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPsdMask.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPsdMaskDs
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPsdMask.description: The downstream PSD mask applicable at the U-C2 reference point. This parameter is used only for G.992.5 and it may impose PSD restrictions (breakpoints) in addition to the Limit PSD mask defined in G.992.5. This is a string of 32 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1. Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint. Octets 6-8 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint. This architecture continues until octets 94-95, which are associated with a 32nd breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 1 and NSCds. Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). But the range of start-bin and end-bin is in range 0 to 195 (0 to -97.5dBm/Hz). Two break points (6 byte) are reserved for start sub-carrier index and end sub-carrier index. So the range of size is 6 up to 96. When the number of breakpoints is less than 32, all remaining octets are set to the value 0. Note that the content of this object should be correlated with the sub-carriers mask and with the RFI setup.

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPSDMASK.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPSDMASKdsEnable
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPSDMASK.description: User custom PSD mask-related parameter used by the ATU-C to use user custom PSD mask. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 and ADSL2plus ).

sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPSDMASK.name: sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPSDMASKdsRequestResult
sheAdslLineConfExtnProfileControlPSDMASK.description: The result of the last psd commmand

sheAdslLineTable.name: sheAdslLineTable
sheAdslLineTable.description: This table includes common attributes describing both ends of the line. It is required for all ADSL physical interfaces. ADSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to adsl(94).

sheAdslLineCoding.name: sheAdslLineCoding
sheAdslLineCoding.description: Specifies the ADSL coding type used on this line.

sheAdslLineType.name: sheAdslLineType
sheAdslLineType.description: Shows the type of ADSL physical line entity that exists, by defining whether and how the line is channelized. If the line is channelized, the value will be other than noChannel(1). This object shows which channel type(s) are currently supported. This values are possible: no channels exist (maybe line is not accessible) fast channel exists only (singleLatency) interleaved channel exists only (singleLatency) fast and interleaved channel exist (dualLatency)

sheAdslLineSpecific.name: sheAdslLineSpecific
sheAdslLineSpecific.description: OID instance in vendor-specific MIB. The Instance may be used to determine shelf/slot/port of the ATUC interface in a DSLAM.

sheAdslLineConfProfile.name: sheAdslLineConfProfile
sheAdslLineConfProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ADSL Line Configuration Profile Table, which applies for this ADSL line, and channels if applicable. A 'DEFVAL' profile will always be exist and set per default.

sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfile.name: sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfile
sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ADSL Line Alarm Configuration Profile Table, which applies to this ADSL line, and channels if applicable. A 'DEFAULT' profile will always be exist and set.

sheAdslLineAction.name: sheAdslLineAction
sheAdslLineAction.description: This object indicates parameter that allows actions on a per line basis. These actions include abort, startup, and tests.

sheAdslLineLineDmtTrellis.name: sheAdslLineLineDmtTrellis
sheAdslLineLineDmtTrellis.description: Parameter that indicates whether trellis coding has been enabled or disabled. Trellis coding should always be enabled for its clear performance advantage. trellisOn(1), trellisOff(2)

sheAdslLineUtopiaL2RxAddr.name: sheAdslLineUtopiaL2RxAddr
sheAdslLineUtopiaL2RxAddr.description: This object indicates UTOPIA Level 2 Rx address for a line.

sheAdslLineUtopiaL2TxAddr.name: sheAdslLineUtopiaL2TxAddr
sheAdslLineUtopiaL2TxAddr.description: This object indicates UTOPIA Level 2 Tx address for a line.

sheAdslLineClockType.name: sheAdslLineClockType
sheAdslLineClockType.description: This object indicates parameter to set use of either crystal or oscillator.

sheAdslLineAtucCapability.name: sheAdslLineAtucCapability
sheAdslLineAtucCapability.description: The capability of co-side. Be aware that multiple bits could be set! Each bit set to 1 means, that the corresponding standart is supported.

sheAdslLineAturCapability.name: sheAdslLineAturCapability
sheAdslLineAturCapability.description: The capability of remote-side. Only available if line has trained - otherwise 0. Be aware that multiple bits could be set! Each bit set to 1 means, that the corresponding standart is supported.

sheAdslLineAtuActualCapability.name: sheAdslLineAtuActualCapability
sheAdslLineAtuActualCapability.description: The actual used capability of the line. Only available if line has trained - otherwise 0. Each bit set to 1 means, that the corresponding standart is supported.

sheAdslLinePwrMgmtPMSF.name: sheAdslLinePwrMgmtPMSF
sheAdslLinePwrMgmtPMSF.description: This object indicates the action that forces a change in the line state of power management. (Not available for ADSL G992.1) Valid values: pmsfL0ToL2StateForce(1) -> testmode, set running line to L2 power safe mode pmsfL2ToL0StateForce(3) -> switch back line from L2 power safe mode to full power L0 state The transitions pmsfL3ToL0StateForce (unlock) and pmsfL3StateForce (lock) should always be done via ifAdminState setting.

sheAdslLineDeltConfLDSF.name: sheAdslLineDeltConfLDSF
sheAdslLineDeltConfLDSF.description: DELT-related parameter used by the ATU-C to force the line into loop diagnostics mode. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 and ADSL2plus ).

sheAdslLineRfiBandMask.name: sheAdslLineRfiBandMask
sheAdslLineRfiBandMask.description: BitMask for used sheAdslRfiBandIndex. A Bit-Position correspond's with an index in sheAdslRfiBandTable and mark configured RFI bands they are used for this profile.

sheAdslLineDpboProfile.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfile
sheAdslLineDpboProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the AdslLineDpboProfile Table, which applies for this ADSL line. No 'DEFVAL' profile will exist. Per default no profile is assigned!

sheAdslLineControlRequest.name: sheAdslLineControlRequest
sheAdslLineControlRequest.description: modifyAdslLineEntry: sheAdslLineControlIndex sheAdslLineControlConfProfile sheAdslLineControlAction modifyAdslLineAlarmConfProfileEntry: sheAdslLineControlIndex sheAdslLineControlAlarmConfProfile forceAdslLinePwrMgmtState: vheAdslLineControlIndex sheAdslLineControlPwrMgmtPMSF modifyAdslLineDeltConfEntry: sheAdslLineControlIndex sheAdslLineControlDeltConfLDSF modifyAdslLineRfiBandMask: sheAdslLineControlIndex sheAdslLineControlRfiBandMask ##New for SHR R2.6 setAdslLineDpboProfileEntry: sheAdslLineControlIndex sheAdslLineControlDpboProfile

sheAdslLineControlStatus.name: sheAdslLineControlStatus
sheAdslLineControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheAdslLineControlTimer.name: sheAdslLineControlTimer
sheAdslLineControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheAdslLineControlReqResult.name: sheAdslLineControlReqResult
sheAdslLineControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheAdslLineControlTimeStamp.name: sheAdslLineControlTimeStamp
sheAdslLineControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheAdslLineControlConfProfile.name: sheAdslLineControlConfProfile
sheAdslLineControlConfProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ADSL Line Configuration Profile Table, (adslLineConfProfileTable), which applies for this ADSL line, and channels if applicable. For the used `dynamic' mode, in the case which the configuration profile has not been set, the value will be set to `DEFVAL'.

sheAdslLineControlAlarmConfProfile.name: sheAdslLineControlAlarmConfProfile
sheAdslLineControlAlarmConfProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ADSL Line Alarm Configuration Profile Table, (adslLineAlarmConfProfileTable), which applies to this ADSL line, and channels if applicable. For the used `dynamic' mode, in the case which the alarm profile has not been set, the value will be set to `DEFVAL'.

sheAdslLineControlAction.name: sheAdslLineControlAction
sheAdslLineControlAction.description: This object indicates parameter that allows actions on a per line basis. These actions include abort, startup, and tests.

sheAdslLineControlPwrMgmtPMSF.name: sheAdslLineControlPwrMgmtPMSF
sheAdslLineControlPwrMgmtPMSF.description: Force a change in the line state of power management. (Not available for ADSL G992.1) Valid values: pmsfL0ToL2StateForce(1) -> testmode, set running line to L2 power safe mode pmsfL2ToL0StateForce(3) -> switch back line from L2 power safe mode to full power L0 state The transitions pmsfL3ToL0StateForce (unlock) and pmsfL3StateForce (lock) should always be done via ifAdminState setting.

sheAdslLineControlDeltConfLDSF.name: sheAdslLineControlDeltConfLDSF
sheAdslLineControlDeltConfLDSF.description: DELT-related parameter used by the ATU-C to force the line into loop diagnostics mode. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 and ADSL2plus ).

sheAdslLineControlDpboProfile.name: sheAdslLineControlDpboProfile
sheAdslLineControlDpboProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the AdslLineDpboProfile Table, which applies for this ADSL line.

sheAdslAtucPhysTable.name: sheAdslAtucPhysTable
sheAdslAtucPhysTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC. Each row contains the Physical Layer Parameters table for that ATUC. ADSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to adsl(94).

sheAdslAtucPhysInvSerialNumber.name: sheAdslAtucPhysInvSerialNumber
sheAdslAtucPhysInvSerialNumber.description: The vendor specific string that identifies the vendor equipment.

sheAdslAtucPhysInvVendorID.name: sheAdslAtucPhysInvVendorID
sheAdslAtucPhysInvVendorID.description: The vendor ID code is a copy of the binary vendor identification field defined by the PHY[10] and expressed as readable characters.

sheAdslAtucPhysInvVersionNumber.name: sheAdslAtucPhysInvVersionNumber
sheAdslAtucPhysInvVersionNumber.description: The vendor specific version number sent by this ATU as part of the initialization messages. It is a copy of the binary version number field defined by the PHY[10] and expressed as readable characters.

sheAdslAtucPhysCurrSnrMgn.name: sheAdslAtucPhysCurrSnrMgn
sheAdslAtucPhysCurrSnrMgn.description: Noise Margin as seen by this ATU with respect to its received signal in tenth dB.

sheAdslAtucPhysCurrAtn.name: sheAdslAtucPhysCurrAtn
sheAdslAtucPhysCurrAtn.description: Measured difference in the total power transmitted by the peer ATU and the total power received by this ATU.

sheAdslAtucPhysCurrStatus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysCurrStatus
sheAdslAtucPhysCurrStatus.description: Indicates current state of the ATUC line. This is a bit-map of possible conditions. The various bit positions are: 0 noDefect There no defects on the line 1 lossOfFraming ATUC failure due to not receiving valid frame. 2 lossOfSignal ATUC failure due to not receiving signal. 3 lossOfPower ATUC failure due to loss of power. Note: the Agent may still function. 4 lossOfSignalQuality Loss of Signal Quality is declared when the Noise Margin falls below the Minimum Noise Margin, or the bit-error-rate exceeds 10^-7. 5 lossOfLink ATUC failure due to inability to link with ATUR. 6 dataInitFailure ATUC failure during initialization due to bit errors corrupting startup exchange data. 7 configInitFailure ATUC failure during initialization due to peer ATU not able to support requested configuration 8 protocolInitFailure ATUC failure during initialization due to incompatible protocol used by the peer ATU. 9 noPeerAtuPresent ATUC failure during initialization due to no activation sequence detected from peer ATU. This is intended to supplement ifOperStatus.

sheAdslAtucPhysCurrOutputPwr.name: sheAdslAtucPhysCurrOutputPwr
sheAdslAtucPhysCurrOutputPwr.description: Measured total output power transmitted by this ATU. This is the measurement that was reported during the last activation sequence.

sheAdslAtucPhysCurrAttainableRate.name: sheAdslAtucPhysCurrAttainableRate
sheAdslAtucPhysCurrAttainableRate.description: Indicates the maximum currently attainable data rate by the ATU. This value will be equal or greater than the current line rate.

sheAdslAtucPhysOpState.name: sheAdslAtucPhysOpState
sheAdslAtucPhysOpState.description: This object indicates the operational state of the ATU. Values include idle,handshake, training, Delt mode (loop diagnostic mode), etc. idle(0), data(1), bootUpLoad(8), handshake(16), training(24), framerSync(26), fastRetrainInProg(27), llTest(128), dlTest(131), txTest(132), atmLpTest(133), discovery(46), deltTraining(139), delt(140)

sheAdslAtucPhysActualStd.name: sheAdslAtucPhysActualStd
sheAdslAtucPhysActualStd.description: This object provides actual ATU-C configuration based on outcome of negotiation with ATU-R. In this case, the parameter provides actual standard used for the connection.

sheAdslAtucPhysBertError.name: sheAdslAtucPhysBertError
sheAdslAtucPhysBertError.description: This object indicates the No. of bit errors detected during BERT.

sheAdslAtucPhysTxAtmCellCounter.name: sheAdslAtucPhysTxAtmCellCounter
sheAdslAtucPhysTxAtmCellCounter.description: This object Provides transmit ATM cell counter.

sheAdslAtucPhysRxAtmCellCounter.name: sheAdslAtucPhysRxAtmCellCounter
sheAdslAtucPhysRxAtmCellCounter.description: This object Provides receive ATM cell counter.

sheAdslAtucPhysStartProgress.name: sheAdslAtucPhysStartProgress
sheAdslAtucPhysStartProgress.description: This object provides current detailed start up information to be used for debugging.

sheAdslAtucPhysBertSync.name: sheAdslAtucPhysBertSync
sheAdslAtucPhysBertSync.description: Indicates if the Signal is in Sync or not.

sheAdslAtucPhysParametricTestResult.name: sheAdslAtucPhysParametricTestResult
sheAdslAtucPhysParametricTestResult.description: Indicates the Result of the Parametric Test conducted on the Xcvr.

sheAdslAtucPwrMgmtState.name: sheAdslAtucPwrMgmtState
sheAdslAtucPwrMgmtState.description: Line Power Management State. (Not valid for ADSL G992.1)

sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLINSCus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLINSCus
sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLINSCus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the scale factor to be applied to the upstream Hlin(f) values. Only available after a loop diagnostic procedure. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus).

sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLINpsus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLINpsus
sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLINpsus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of complex upstream Hlin(f) values in linear scale. Every two octects refer to one element in this array of octets. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus). This parameter is an array of complex upstream Hlin(f) values in linear scale. Each array entry represents the Hlin(f = i*HLINGus* delta(f)) value for a particular subcarrier group index i, ranging from 0 to MIN(NSCus - 1,511). The Hlin(f) is represented as ((scale/2(exp15))*((a(i) + j*b(i))/2(exp15))), with scale being coded as a 16-bit unsigned integer and, a(i) and b(i) coded as 16-bit 2s complement signed integers in the (-2(exp15) + 1) to (+2(exp15) - 1) range. A special value a(i) = b(i) = -2(exp15) indicates that no measurement could be done for this subcarrier group because it is out of the passband or that the attenuation is out of range to be represented. This parameter is only available after a loop diagnostic procedure.

sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLOGMTus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLOGMTus
sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLOGMTus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the number of symbols used to measure the upstream Hlog(f). (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus).

sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLOGpsus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLOGpsus
sheAdslAtucPhysDeltHLOGpsus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of real upstream Hlog(f) values in dB. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus). This parameter is an array of real upstream Hlog(f) values in dB. Each array entry represents the real Hlog(f = i*HLOGGus* delta(f)) value for a particular subcarrier group sub-carrier index i, ranging from 0 to MIN(NSCus - 1,511). The real Hlog(f) value is represented as (6 - m(i)/10), with m(i) 10-bit unsigned integer in the 0 to 1022 range. A special value m = 1023 indicates that no measurement could be done for this subcarrier group because it is out of the passband or that the attenuation is out of range to be represented.

sheAdslAtucPhysDeltQLNMTus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysDeltQLNMTus
sheAdslAtucPhysDeltQLNMTus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the number of symbols used to measure the upstream QLN(f) values. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus).

sheAdslAtucPhysDeltQLNpsus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysDeltQLNpsus
sheAdslAtucPhysDeltQLNpsus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of real upstream QLN(f) values in dBm/Hz. Every two octects refer to one element in this array of octets. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus) This parameter is an array of real upstream QLN(f) values in dBm/Hz. Each array entry represents the QLN(f = i*QLNGus* delta(f)) value for a particular subcarrier group index i, ranging from 0 to MIN(NSCus - 1,511). The QLN(f) is represented as (-23 - n(i)/2), with n(i) an 8-bit unsigned integer in the 0 to 254 range. A special value n(i) = 255 indicates that no measurement could be done for this subcarrier group because it is out of the passband or that the noise PSD is out of range to be represented.

sheAdslAtucPhysActState.name: sheAdslAtucPhysActState
sheAdslAtucPhysActState.description: This object indicates the result of the ATU's line activation. Values include no error etc.

sheAdslAtucPhysCurrentBinStatus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysCurrentBinStatus
sheAdslAtucPhysCurrentBinStatus.description: This parameter represent the current bin status of used subcarriers. Each octet map to the corresponding bin.

sheAdslAtucPhysCurrentBinBitLoading.name: sheAdslAtucPhysCurrentBinBitLoading
sheAdslAtucPhysCurrentBinBitLoading.description: This parameter represent the current used bit loading per bin in upstream direction. Each octet map to the corresponding bin.

sheAdslAtucPhysDeltSNRMTus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysDeltSNRMTus
sheAdslAtucPhysDeltSNRMTus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the number of symbols used to measure the upstream SNR(f) values. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus) It is represented as a 16-bit unsigned value. After a loop diagnostic procedure, this parameter shall contain the number of symbols used to generate the associate parameter. It should correspond to the value specified in the Recommendation (e.g., the number of symbols in 1 s time interval for G.992.3).

sheAdslAtucPhysDeltDMTBinSNRus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysDeltDMTBinSNRus
sheAdslAtucPhysDeltDMTBinSNRus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of real upstream SNR(f) values in dB (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus) It is coded in the same way as the related downstream parameter.

sheAdslAtucPhysDeltLastTxState.name: sheAdslAtucPhysDeltLastTxState
sheAdslAtucPhysDeltLastTxState.description: DELT-related parameter that provides last successful transmitted initialization state by the ATU-C. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus) Initialization states are defined in the individual ADSL Recommendations and are counted from 0 (if G.994.1 is used) or 1 (if G.994.1 is not used) up to Showtime. This parameter must be interpreted along with the ADSL Transmission System. This parameter is available only when, after a failed full initialization, the line diagnostics procedures are activated on the line. Line diagnostics procedures can be activated by the operator of the system (through the Line State Forced line configuration parameter) or autonomously by the ATU-C or ATU-R.

sheAdslAtucPhysDeltSATNus.name: sheAdslAtucPhysDeltSATNus
sheAdslAtucPhysDeltSATNus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the uptream signal attenuation (length = 4 bytes). (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus). This parameter is the measured difference in dB in the total power transmitted by the ATU-R and the total power received by the ATU-C over all subcarriers during showtime. The upstream line attenuation ranges from 0 to +127 dB with 0.1 dB steps. A special value indicates the line attenuation is out of range to be represented. NOTE: During showtime, only a subset of the subcarriers may be transmitted by the ATU-R, as compared to diagnostics mode and initialization. Therefore, the upstream Signal attenuation may be significantly lower than the upstream Line attenuation.

sheAdslAtucChanTable.name: sheAdslAtucChanTable
sheAdslAtucChanTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC channel.

sheAdslAtucChanEntry.name: sheAdslAtucChanEntry
sheAdslAtucChanEntry.description: An entry in the adslAtucChanTable. This table is only supported by NE releases smaller then R2.5 (NO dualLatency support)!!

sheAdslAtucChanInterleaveDelay.name: sheAdslAtucChanInterleaveDelay
sheAdslAtucChanInterleaveDelay.description: Interleave Delay for this channel. Interleave delay applies only to the interleave channel and defines the mapping (relative spacing) between subsequent input bytes at the interleaver input and their placement in the bit stream at the interleaver output. Larger numbers provide greater separation between consecutive input bytes in the output bit stream allowing for improved impulse noise immunity at the expense of payload latency. In the case where the ifType is Fast(125), use noSuchObject.

sheAdslAtucChanCurrTxRate.name: sheAdslAtucChanCurrTxRate
sheAdslAtucChanCurrTxRate.description: Actual transmit rate on this channel.

sheAdslAtucChanPrevTxRate.name: sheAdslAtucChanPrevTxRate
sheAdslAtucChanPrevTxRate.description: The rate at the time of the last adslAtucRateChangeTrap event. It is also set at initialization to prevent a trap being sent. Rate changes less than adslAtucThresh(*)RateDown or less than adslAtucThresh(*)RateUp will not cause a trap or cause this object to change. (*) == Fast or Interleave. See AdslLineAlarmConfProfileEntry.

sheAdslAtucChanCrcBlockLength.name: sheAdslAtucChanCrcBlockLength
sheAdslAtucChanCrcBlockLength.description: Indicates the length of the channel data-block on which the CRC operates. Refer to Line Code Specific MIBs, [11] and [12] for more information.

sheAdslAtucChanCurrAtmStatus.name: sheAdslAtucChanCurrAtmStatus
sheAdslAtucChanCurrAtmStatus.description: indicates an ncd or lcd failure if the counter surpasses 127. If neither ATM counter surpasses 127, the return value will be 'NoAtmDefect'. noAtmDefect(0), noCellDeleniation(1), lossOfCellDeleniation(2)

sheAdslAtucChanRsSymbols.name: sheAdslAtucChanRsSymbols
sheAdslAtucChanRsSymbols.description: Indicates number of DMT symbols per Reed-Solomon code word (S) in the downstream direction. Note that S is not restricted to interleaved mode only. Even in fast mode, S is a valid constant value and is equal to 1.

sheAdslAtucChanRsDepth.name: sheAdslAtucChanRsDepth
sheAdslAtucChanRsDepth.description: Indicates interleaving depth (D) in the downstream direction. Note that D is not restricted to interleaved mode only. Even in fast mode, D is a valid constant value and is equal to 1.

sheAdslAtucChanRsRedundancy.name: sheAdslAtucChanRsRedundancy
sheAdslAtucChanRsRedundancy.description: Indicates number of redundant bytes (R) per Reed-Solomon code in the downstream direction.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataTable.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataTable
sheAdslAtucPerfDataTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC. ADSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to adsl(94).

sheAdslAtucPerfDataLofs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataLofs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataLofs.description: Count of the number of Loss of Framing failures since agent reset.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataLoss.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataLoss
sheAdslAtucPerfDataLoss.description: Count of the number of Loss of Signal failures since agent reset.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataLols.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataLols
sheAdslAtucPerfDataLols.description: Count of the number of Loss of Link failures since agent reset.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataLprs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataLprs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataLprs.description: Count of the number of Loss of Power failures since agent reset.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataESs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataESs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataESs.description: Count of the number of Errored Seconds since agent reset. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los or sef defects.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataInits.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataInits
sheAdslAtucPerfDataInits.description: Count of the line initialization attempts since agent reset. Includes both successful and failed attempts.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatFastR.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatFastR
sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatFastR.description: The value of this object indicates the count of fast retrains.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatFailedFastR.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatFailedFastR
sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatFailedFastR.description: The value of this object indicates the count of failed fast retrains.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatSesL.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatSesL
sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatSesL.description: The value of this object indicates the count of severely errored second line.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatUasL.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatUasL
sheAdslAtucPerfDataStatUasL.description: The value of this object indicates the count of unavailable errored seconds.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataValidIntervals.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataValidIntervals
sheAdslAtucPerfDataValidIntervals.description: The number of previous 15-minute intervals in the interval table for which data was collected. Given that <n> is the maximum # of intervals supported. The value will be <n> unless the measurement was (re-)started within the last (<n>*15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals for which the agent has at least some data. In certain cases (e.g., in the case where the agent is a proxy) it is possible that some intervals are unavailable. In this case, this interval is the maximum interval number for which data is available.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataInvalidIntervals.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataInvalidIntervals
sheAdslAtucPerfDataInvalidIntervals.description: The number of intervals in the range from 0 to the value of adslAtucPerfValidIntervals for which no data is available. This object will typically be zero except in cases where the data for some intervals are not available (e.g., in proxy situations).

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElapsed.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElapsed
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElapsed.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLofs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLofs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLofs.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was Loss of Framing.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLoss.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLoss
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLoss.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was Loss of Signal.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLols.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLols
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLols.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was Loss of Link.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLprs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLprs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinLprs.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was Loss of Power.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinESs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinESs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds in the current 15 minute interval. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los or sef defects.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinInits.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinInits
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinInits.description: Count of the line initialization attempts in the current 15 minute interval. Includes both successful and failed attempts.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinFastR.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinFastR
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinFastR.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was fast retrains. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.1

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinFailedFastR.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinFailedFastR
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinFailedFastR.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was failed fast retrains. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.2

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinSesL.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinSesL
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinSesL.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was severely errored seconds. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.7

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinUasL.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinUasL
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr15MinUasL.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was count for unavailable errored seconds. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.9
