sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElapsed.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElapsed
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElapsed.description: Number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current 1-day interval.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLofs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLofs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLofs.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Framing during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLoss.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLoss
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLoss.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Signal during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLols.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLols
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLols.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Link during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLprs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLprs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayLprs.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Power during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayESs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayESs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los or sef defects.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayInits.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayInits
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayInits.description: Count of the line initialization attempts in the day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed. Includes both successful and failed attempts.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayFastR.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayFastR
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayFastR.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was fast retrains during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1Day TimeElapsed. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.1

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayFailedFastR.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayFailedFastR
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayFailedFastR.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was failed fast retrains during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1Day TimeElapsed.REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.2

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DaySesL.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DaySesL
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DaySesL.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Severely Errored Seconds during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.7

sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayUasL.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayUasL
sheAdslAtucPerfDataCurr1DayUasL.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Unavailable Errored Seconds during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.9

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayTimeElapsed.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayTimeElapsed
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayTimeElapsed.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval in seconds.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs.description: The amount of time in the previous 1-day interval over which the performance monitoring information is actually counted. This value will be the same as the interval duration except in a situation where performance monitoring data could not be collected for any reason.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLofs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLofs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLofs.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Framing within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLoss.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLoss
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLoss.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Signal within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLols.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLols
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLols.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Link within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLprs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLprs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayLprs.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Power within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayESs.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayESs
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds within the most recent previous 1-day period. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los or sef defects.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayInits.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayInits
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayInits.description: Count of the line initialization attempts in the most recent previous 1-day period. Includes both successful and failed attempts.

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayFastR.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayFastR
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayFastR.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was fast retrains within the most recent previous 1 day period. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.1

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayFailedFastR.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayFailedFastR
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayFailedFastR.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was failed fast retrains within the most recent previous 1 day period. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.2

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DaySesL.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DaySesL
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DaySesL.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was severely errored seconds within the most recent previous 1 day period. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.7

sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayUasL.name: sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayUasL
sheAdslAtucPerfDataPrev1DayUasL.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was unavailable errored seconds within the most recent previous 1 day period. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.9

sheAdslAtucIntervalTable.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalTable
sheAdslAtucIntervalTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC performance data collection interval. ADSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to adsl(94).

sheAdslAtucIntervalNumber.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalNumber
sheAdslAtucIntervalNumber.description: Performance Data Interval number 1 is the the most recent previous interval; interval 96 is 24 hours ago. Intervals 2..96 are optional.

sheAdslAtucIntervalValidData.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalValidData
sheAdslAtucIntervalValidData.description: This variable indicates if the data for this interval is valid.

sheAdslAtucIntervalEndTime.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalEndTime
sheAdslAtucIntervalEndTime.description: This variable indicates the time of storing this interval.

sheAdslAtucIntervalLofs.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalLofs
sheAdslAtucIntervalLofs.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Framing.

sheAdslAtucIntervalLoss.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalLoss
sheAdslAtucIntervalLoss.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Signal.

sheAdslAtucIntervalLols.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalLols
sheAdslAtucIntervalLols.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Link.

sheAdslAtucIntervalLprs.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalLprs
sheAdslAtucIntervalLprs.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Power.

sheAdslAtucIntervalESs.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalESs
sheAdslAtucIntervalESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds in the interval. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los or sef defects.

sheAdslAtucIntervalInits.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalInits
sheAdslAtucIntervalInits.description: Count of the line initialization attempts during the interval. Includes both successful and failed attempts.

sheAdslAtucIntervalFastR.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalFastR
sheAdslAtucIntervalFastR.description: This variable indicates Count of seconds in the interval when there was Fast Retrains.

sheAdslAtucIntervalFailedFastR.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalFailedFastR
sheAdslAtucIntervalFailedFastR.description: This variable indicates Count of seconds in the interval when there was Failed Fast Retrains.

sheAdslAtucIntervalSesL.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalSesL
sheAdslAtucIntervalSesL.description: This variable indicates Count of seconds in the interval when there was severely errored seconds.

sheAdslAtucIntervalUasL.name: sheAdslAtucIntervalUasL
sheAdslAtucIntervalUasL.description: This variable indicates Count of seconds in the interval when there was unavailable errored seconds.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataTable.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataTable
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC channel.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataEntry.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataEntry
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataEntry.description: An entry in adslAtucChanPerfDataTable. This table is only supported by NE releases smaller then R2.5 (NO dualLatency support)!!

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataTimeElapsed.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataTimeElapsed
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataTimeElapsed.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataReceivedBlks.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataReceivedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataReceivedBlks.description: Count of all encoded blocks received on this channel since agent reset.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataTransmittedBlks.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataTransmittedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataTransmittedBlks.description: Count of all encoded blocks transmitted on this channel since agent reset.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCorrectedBlks.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCorrectedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCorrectedBlks.description: Count of all blocks received with errors that were corrected since agent reset. These blocks are passed on as good data.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataUncorrectBlks.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataUncorrectBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataUncorrectBlks.description: Count of all blocks received with uncorrectable errors since agent reset.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataNcd.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataNcd
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataNcd.description: Count of no cell delineation(ncd) on this channel.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataOcd.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataOcd
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataOcd.description: Count of out of cell delineation (ocd) on this channel.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataHec.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataHec
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataHec.description: Header error check counter(hec) on this channel.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataValidIntervals.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataValidIntervals
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataValidIntervals.description: The number of previous 15-minute intervals in the interval table for which data was collected. Given that <n> is the maximum # of intervals supported. The value will be <n> unless the measurement was (re-)started within the last (<n>*15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals for which the agent has at least some data. In certain cases (e.g., in the case where the agent is a proxy) it is possible that some intervals are unavailable. In this case, this interval is the maximum interval number for which data is available.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataInvalidIntervals.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataInvalidIntervals
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataInvalidIntervals.description: The number of intervals in the range from 0 to the value of adslAtucChanPerfValidIntervals for which no data is available. This object will typically be zero except in cases where the data for some intervals are not available (e.g., in proxy situations).

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElap.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElapsed
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElap.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinReceived.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinReceivedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinReceived.description: Count of all encoded blocks received on this channel within the current 15 minute interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinTransmit.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinTransmittedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinTransmit.description: Count of all encoded blocks transmitted on this channel within the current 15 minute interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinCorrecte.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinCorrectedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinCorrecte.description: Count of all blocks received with errors that were corrected on this channel within the current 15 minute interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinUncorrec.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinUncorrectBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinUncorrec.description: Count of all blocks received with uncorrectable errors on this channel within the current 15 minute interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinNcd.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinNcd
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinNcd.description: Count of no cell delineation(ncd) on this channel within the current 15 minute time interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinOcd.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinOcd
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinOcd.description: Count of out of cell delineation (ocd) on this channel within the current 15 minute time interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinHec.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinHec
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr15MinHec.description: Header error check counter(hec) on this channel within the current 15 minute time interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElaps.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElapsed
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElaps.description: Number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current 1-day interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayReceivedB.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayReceivedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayReceivedB.description: Count of all encoded blocks received on this channel during the current day as measured by adslAtucChanPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayTransmitt.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayTransmittedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayTransmitt.description: Count of all encoded blocks transmitted on this channel during the current day as measured by adslAtucChanPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayCorrected.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayCorrectedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayCorrected.description: Count of all blocks received with errors that were corrected on this channel during the current day as measured by adslAtucChanPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayUncorrect.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayUncorrectBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayUncorrect.description: Count of all blocks received with uncorrectable errors on this channel during the current day as measured by adslAtucChanPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayNcd.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayNcd
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayNcd.description: Count of no cell delineation (ncd) on this channel within the current 1 day time interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayOcd.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayOcd
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayOcd.description: Count of out of cell delineation (ocd) on this channel within the current 1 day time interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayHec.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayHec
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataCurr1DayHec.description: Header error check counter (hec) on this channel within the current 1 day time interval.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs.description: The amount of time in the previous 1-day interval over which the performance monitoring information is actually counted. This value will be the same as the interval duration except in a situation where performance monitoring data could not be collected for any reason.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayReceivedB.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayReceivedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayReceivedB.description: Count of all encoded blocks received on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayTransmitt.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayTransmittedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayTransmitt.description: Count of all encoded blocks transmitted on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayCorrected.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayCorrectedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayCorrected.description: Count of all blocks received with errors that were corrected on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayUncorrect.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayUncorrectBlks
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayUncorrect.description: Count of all blocks received with uncorrectable errors on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayNcd.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayNcd
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayNcd.description: Count of no cell delineation (ncd) on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayOcd.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayOcd
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayOcd.description: Count of out of cell delineation (ocd) on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayHec.name: sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayHec
sheAdslAtucChanPerfDataPrev1DayHec.description: Header error check counter(hec) on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalTable.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalTable
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC channel's performance data collection interval.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalEntry.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalEntry
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the adslAtucIntervalTable. This table is only supported by NE releases smaller then R2.5 (NO dualLatency support)!!

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalNumber.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalNumber
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalNumber.description: Performance Data Interval number 1 is the the most recent previous interval; interval 96 is 24 hours ago. Intervals 2..96 are optional.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalValidData.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalValidData
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalValidData.description: This variable indicates if the data for this interval is valid.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalEndTime.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalEndTime
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalEndTime.description: This variable indicates the time of storing this interval.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalReceivedBlks.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalReceivedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalReceivedBlks.description: Count of all encoded blocks received on this channel during this interval.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalTransmittedBlks.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalTransmittedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalTransmittedBlks.description: Count of all encoded blocks transmitted on this channel during this interval.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalCorrectedBlks.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalCorrectedBlks
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalCorrectedBlks.description: Count of all blocks received with errors that were corrected on this channel during this interval.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalUncorrectBlks.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalUncorrectBlks
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalUncorrectBlks.description: Count of all blocks received with uncorrectable errors on this channel during this interval.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalNcd.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalNcd
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalNcd.description: Indicates count of no cell delineation on this channel for this interval.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalOcd.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalOcd
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalOcd.description: Indicates count of out cell delineation on this channel for this interval.

sheAdslAtucChanIntervalHec.name: sheAdslAtucChanIntervalHec
sheAdslAtucChanIntervalHec.description: Indicates Header error check counter on this channel during this interval.

sheAdslAturPhysTable.name: sheAdslAturPhysTable
sheAdslAturPhysTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUR Each row contains the Physical Layer Parameters table for that ATUR. ADSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to adsl(94).

sheAdslAturPhysInvSerialNumber.name: sheAdslAturPhysInvSerialNumber
sheAdslAturPhysInvSerialNumber.description: The vendor specific string that identifies the vendor equipment.

sheAdslAturPhysInvVendorID.name: sheAdslAturPhysInvVendorID
sheAdslAturPhysInvVendorID.description: The vendor ID code is a copy of the binary vendor identification field defined by the PHY[10] and expressed as readable characters.

sheAdslAturPhysInvVersionNumber.name: sheAdslAturPhysInvVersionNumber
sheAdslAturPhysInvVersionNumber.description: The vendor specific version number sent by this ATU as part of the initialization messages. It is a copy of the binary version number field defined by the PHY[10] and expressed as readable characters.

sheAdslAturPhysCurrSnrMgn.name: sheAdslAturPhysCurrSnrMgn
sheAdslAturPhysCurrSnrMgn.description: Noise Margin as seen by this ATU with respect to its received signal in tenth dB.

sheAdslAturPhysCurrAtn.name: sheAdslAturPhysCurrAtn
sheAdslAturPhysCurrAtn.description: Measured difference in the total power transmitted by the peer ATU and the total power received by this ATU.

sheAdslAturPhysCurrStatus.name: sheAdslAturPhysCurrStatus
sheAdslAturPhysCurrStatus.description: Indicates current state of the ATUR line. This is a bit-map of possible conditions. Due to the isolation of the ATUR when line problems occur, many state conditions like loss of power, loss of quality signal, and initialization errors, can not be determined. While trouble shooting ATUR, also use object, adslAtucCurrStatus. The various bit positions are: 0 noDefect There no defects on the line 1 lossOfFraming ATUR failure due to not receiving valid frame 2 lossOfSignal ATUR failure due to not receiving signal 3 lossOfPower ATUR failure due to loss of power 4 lossOfSignalQuality Loss of Signal Quality is declared when the Noise Margin falls below the Minimum Noise Margin, or the bit-error-rate exceeds 10^-7. This is intended to supplement ifOperStatus.

sheAdslAturPhysCurrOutputPwr.name: sheAdslAturPhysCurrOutputPwr
sheAdslAturPhysCurrOutputPwr.description: Measured total output power transmitted by this ATU. This is the measurement that was reported during the last activation sequence.

sheAdslAturPhysCurrAttainableRate.name: sheAdslAturPhysCurrAttainableRate
sheAdslAturPhysCurrAttainableRate.description: Indicates the maximum currently attainable data rate by the ATU. This value will be equal or greater than the current line rate.

sheAdslAturPhysConfig.name: sheAdslAturPhysConfig
sheAdslAturPhysConfig.description: This object provides the upstream and downstream ATU-R configuration data (EOC - read 5 sec after data mode).

sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLINSCds.name: sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLINSCds
sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLINSCds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the scale factor to be applied to the downstream Hlin(f) values. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus).

sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLINpsds.name: sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLINpsds
sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLINpsds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of complex downstream Hlin(f) values in linear scale. Every two octects refer to one element in this array of octets. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus). This parameter is an array of complex downstream Hlin(f) values in linear scale. Each array entry represents the Hlin(f = i*HLINGds* delta(f)) value for a particular subcarrier group index i, ranging from 0 to MIN(NSCds - 1,511). The Hlin(f) is represented as ((scale/2(exp15))*((a(i) + j*b(i))/2(exp15))), with scale being coded as a 16-bit unsigned integer and, a(i) and b(i) coded as 16-bit 2s complement signed integers in the (-2(exp15) + 1) to (+2(exp15) - 1) range. A special value a(i) = b(i) = -2(exp15) indicates that no measurement could be done for this subcarrier group because it is out of the passband or that the attenuation is out of range to be represented. This parameter is only available after a loop diagnostic procedure.

sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLOGMTds.name: sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLOGMTds
sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLOGMTds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the number of symbols used to measure the downstream Hlog(f). (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus).

sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLOGpsds.name: sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLOGpsds
sheAdslAturPhysDeltHLOGpsds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of real downstream Hlog(f) values in dB. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus). This parameter is an array of real downstream Hlog(f) values in dB. Each array entry represents the real Hlog(f = i*HLOGGds* delta(f)) value for a particular subcarrier group sub-carrier index i, ranging from 0 to MIN(NSCds - 1,511). The real Hlog(f) value is represented as (6 - m(i)/10), with m(i) 10-bit unsigned integer in the 0 to 1022 range. A special value m = 1023 indicates that no measurement could be done for this subcarrier group because it is out of the passband or that the attenuation is out of range to be represented.

sheAdslAturPhysDeltQLNMTds.name: sheAdslAturPhysDeltQLNMTds
sheAdslAturPhysDeltQLNMTds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the number of symbols used to measure the downstream QLN(f) values. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus).

sheAdslAturPhysDeltQLNpsds.name: sheAdslAturPhysDeltQLNpsds
sheAdslAturPhysDeltQLNpsds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of real downstream QLN(f) values in dBm/Hz. Every two octects refer to one element in this array of octets. (Not available for ADSL but ADSL2 & ADSL2plus). This parameter is an array of real downstream QLN(f) values in dBm/Hz. Each array entry represents the QLN(f = i*QLNGds* delta(f)) value for a particular subcarrier group index i, ranging from 0 to MIN(NSCds - 1,511). The QLN(f) is represented as (-23 - n(i)/2), with n(i) an 8-bit unsigned integer in the 0 to 254 range. A special value n(i) = 255 indicates that no measurement could be done for this subcarrier group because it is out of the passband or that the noise PSD is out of range to be represented.

sheAdslAturPhysCurrentBinBitLoading.name: sheAdslAturPhysCurrentBinBitLoading
sheAdslAturPhysCurrentBinBitLoading.description: This parameter represent the current used bit loading per bin in downstream direction. Each octet map to the corresponding bin.

sheAdslAturPhysDeltSNRMTds.name: sheAdslAturPhysDeltSNRMTds
sheAdslAturPhysDeltSNRMTds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the number of symbols used to measure the downstream SNR(f) values. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus) It is represented as a 16-bit unsigned value. After a loop diagnostic procedure, this parameter shall contain the number of symbols used to generate the associate parameter. It should correspond to the value specified in the Recommendation (e.g., the number of symbols in 1 s time interval for G.992.3).

sheAdslAturPhysDeltDMTBinSNRds.name: sheAdslAturPhysDeltDMTBinSNRds
sheAdslAturPhysDeltDMTBinSNRds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of real downstream SNR(f) values in dB (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus) Each array entry represents the SNR(f = i*f) value for a particular subcarrier index i, ranging from 0 to NSCds C 1. The SNR(f) is represented as (C32 + snr(i)/2), with snr(i) an 8-bit unsigned integer in the 0 to 254 range. A special value snr(i) = 255 indicates that no measurement could be done for the subcarrier because it is out of the passband or that the noise PSD is out of range to be represented.

sheAdslAturPhysDeltLastTxState.name: sheAdslAturPhysDeltLastTxState
sheAdslAturPhysDeltLastTxState.description: DELT-related parameter that provides last successful transmitted initialization state by the ATU-R. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus) Initialization states are defined in the individual ADSL Recommendations and are counted from 0 (if G.994.1 is used) or 1 (if G.994.1 is not used) up to Showtime. This parameter must be interpreted along with the ADSL Transmission System. This parameter is available only when, after a failed full initialization, the line diagnostics procedures are activated on the line. Line diagnostics procedures can be activated by the operator of the system (through the Line State Forced line configuration parameter) or autonomously by the ATU-C or ATU-R.

sheAdslAturPhysDeltSATNds.name: sheAdslAturPhysDeltSATNds
sheAdslAturPhysDeltSATNds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the downtream signal attenuation (length = 4 bytes). (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus). This parameter is the measured difference in the total power transmitted by the ATU-C and the total power received by the ATU-R over all subcarriers during showtime. The downstream line attenuation ranges from 0 to +127 dB with 0.1 dB steps. A special value indicates the line attenuation is out of range to be represented. NOTE: During showtime, only a subset of the subcarriers may be transmitted by the ATU-C, as compared to diagnostics mode and initialization. Therefore, the downstream Signal attenuation may be significantly lower than the downstream Line attenuation.

sheAdslAturChanTable.name: sheAdslAturChanTable
sheAdslAturChanTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUR channel.

sheAdslAturChanEntry.name: sheAdslAturChanEntry
sheAdslAturChanEntry.description: An entry in the adslAturChanTable. This table is only supported by NE releases smaller then R2.5 (NO dualLatency support)!!

sheAdslAturChanInterleaveDelay.name: sheAdslAturChanInterleaveDelay
sheAdslAturChanInterleaveDelay.description: Interleave Delay for this channel. Interleave delay applies only to the interleave channel and defines the mapping (relative spacing) between subsequent input bytes at the interleaver input and their placement in the bit stream at the interleaver output. Larger numbers provide greater separation between consecutive input bytes in the output bit stream allowing for improved impulse noise immunity at the expense of payload latency. In the case where the ifType is Fast(125), use noSuchObject.

sheAdslAturChanCurrTxRate.name: sheAdslAturChanCurrTxRate
sheAdslAturChanCurrTxRate.description: Actual transmit rate on this channel.

sheAdslAturChanPrevTxRate.name: sheAdslAturChanPrevTxRate
sheAdslAturChanPrevTxRate.description: The rate at the time of the last adslAturRateChangeTrap event. It is also set at initialization to prevent a trap being sent. Rate changes less than adslAturThresh(*)RateDown or less than adslAturThresh(*)RateUp will not cause a trap or cause this object to change. (*) == Fast or Interleave. See AdslLineAlarmConfProfileEntry.

sheAdslAturChanCrcBlockLength.name: sheAdslAturChanCrcBlockLength
sheAdslAturChanCrcBlockLength.description: Indicates the length of the channel data-block on which the CRC operates. Refer to Line Code Specific MIBs, [11] and [12] for more information.

sheAdslAturChanCurrAtmStatus.name: sheAdslAturChanCurrAtmStatus
sheAdslAturChanCurrAtmStatus.description: This object indicates an ncd or lcd failure if the counter surpasses 127. If neither ATM counter surpasses 127, the return value will be NoAtmDefect. noAtmDefect(0), noCellDeleniation(1), lossOfCellDeleniation(2)

sheAdslAturChanRsSymbols.name: sheAdslAturChanRsSymbols
sheAdslAturChanRsSymbols.description: This object indicates number of DMT symbols per Reed- Solomon code word (S) in the upstream direction Note that S is not restricted to interleaved mode only. Even in fast mode, S is a valid constant value and is equal to 1.

sheAdslAturChanRsDepth.name: sheAdslAturChanRsDepth
sheAdslAturChanRsDepth.description: This object indicates interleaving depth (D) in the upstream direction Note that D is not restricted to interleaved mode only. Even in fast mode, D is a valid constant value and is equal to 1.

sheAdslAturChanRsRedundancy.name: sheAdslAturChanRsRedundancy
sheAdslAturChanRsRedundancy.description: This object indicates number of redundant bytes (R) per Reed-Solomon code in the upstream direction.

sheAdslAturPerfDataTable.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataTable
sheAdslAturPerfDataTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUR. ADSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to adsl(94).

sheAdslAturPerfDataLofs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataLofs
sheAdslAturPerfDataLofs.description: Count of the number of Loss of Framing failures since agent reset.

sheAdslAturPerfDataLoss.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataLoss
sheAdslAturPerfDataLoss.description: Count of the number of Loss of Signal failures since agent reset.

sheAdslAturPerfDataLprs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataLprs
sheAdslAturPerfDataLprs.description: Count of the number of Loss of Power failures since agent reset.

sheAdslAturPerfDataESs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataESs
sheAdslAturPerfDataESs.description: Count of the number of Errored Seconds since agent reset. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los or sef defects.

sheAdslAturPerfDataStatSesL.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataStatSesL
sheAdslAturPerfDataStatSesL.description: The value of this object reports the count of severely errored second-line since the last agent reset.

sheAdslAturPerfDataStatUasL.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataStatUasL
sheAdslAturPerfDataStatUasL.description: The value of this object reports the count of unavailable seconds-line since the last agent reset.

sheAdslAturPerfDataValidIntervals.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataValidIntervals
sheAdslAturPerfDataValidIntervals.description: The number of previous 15-minute intervals in the interval table for which data was collected. Given that <n> is the maximum # of intervals supported. The value will be <n> unless the measurement was (re-)started within the last (<n>*15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals for which the agent has at least some data. In certain cases (e.g., in the case where the agent is a proxy) it is possible that some intervals are unavailable. In this case, this interval is the maximum interval number for which data is available.

sheAdslAturPerfDataInvalidIntervals.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataInvalidIntervals
sheAdslAturPerfDataInvalidIntervals.description: The number of intervals in the range from 0 to the value of adslAturPerfValidIntervals for which no data is available. This object will typically be zero except in cases where the data for some intervals are not available (e.g., in proxy situations).

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElapsed.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElapsed
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElapsed.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinLofs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinLofs
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinLofs.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was Loss of Framing.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinLoss.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinLoss
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinLoss.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was Loss of Signal.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinLprs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinLprs
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinLprs.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was Loss of Power.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinESs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinESs
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds in the current 15 minute interval. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los or sef defects.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinSesL.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinSesL
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinSesL.description: For the current 15-minute interval, adslAturPerfCurr15MinSesL reports the current number of seconds during which there have been severely errored seconds-line.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinUasL.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinUasL
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr15MinUasL.description: For the current 15-minute interval, adslAturPerfCurr15MinUasL reports the current number of seconds during which there have been available seconds-line.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElapsed.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElapsed
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElapsed.description: Number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current 1-day interval.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayLofs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayLofs
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayLofs.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Framing during the current day as measured by adslAturPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayLoss.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayLoss
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayLoss.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Signal during the current day as measured by adslAturPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayLprs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayLprs
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayLprs.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Loss of Power during the current day as measured by adslAturPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayESs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayESs
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds during the current day as measured by adslAturPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los or sef defects.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DaySesL.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DaySesL
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DaySesL.description: For the current day as measured by adslAturPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed [RFC2662], adslAturPerfCurr1DaySesL reports the number of seconds during which there have been severely errored seconds-line.

sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayUasL.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayUasL
sheAdslAturPerfDataCurr1DayUasL.description: For the current day as measured by adslAturPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed [RFC2662], adslAturPerfCurr1DayUasL reports the number of seconds during which there have been unavailable seconds-line.

sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs
sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs.description: The amount of time in the previous 1-day interval over which the performance monitoring information is actually counted. This value will be the same as the interval duration except in a situation where performance monitoring data could not be collected for any reason.

sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayLofs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayLofs
sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayLofs.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Framing within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayLoss.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayLoss
sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayLoss.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Signal within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayLprs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayLprs
sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayLprs.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Power within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayESs.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayESs
sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds within the most recent previous 1-day period. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los or sef defects.

sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DaySesL.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DaySesL
sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DaySesL.description: For the previous day, adslAturPerfPrev1DaySesL reports the number of seconds during which there were severely errored seconds-line.

sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayUasL.name: sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayUasL
sheAdslAturPerfDataPrev1DayUasL.description: For the previous day, adslAturPerfPrev1DayUasL reports the number of seconds during which there were severely errored seconds-line.

sheAdslAturIntervalTable.name: sheAdslAturIntervalTable
sheAdslAturIntervalTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUR performance data collection interval. ADSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to adsl(94).

sheAdslAturIntervalNumber.name: sheAdslAturIntervalNumber
sheAdslAturIntervalNumber.description: Performance Data Interval number 1 is the the most recent previous interval; interval 96 is 24 hours ago. Intervals 2..96 are optional.

sheAdslAturIntervalValidData.name: sheAdslAturIntervalValidData
sheAdslAturIntervalValidData.description: This variable indicates if the data for this interval is valid.

sheAdslAturIntervalEndTime.name: sheAdslAturIntervalEndTime
sheAdslAturIntervalEndTime.description: This variable indicates the time of storing this interval.

sheAdslAturIntervalLofs.name: sheAdslAturIntervalLofs
sheAdslAturIntervalLofs.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Framing.

sheAdslAturIntervalLoss.name: sheAdslAturIntervalLoss
sheAdslAturIntervalLoss.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Signal.

sheAdslAturIntervalLprs.name: sheAdslAturIntervalLprs
sheAdslAturIntervalLprs.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Power.

sheAdslAturIntervalESs.name: sheAdslAturIntervalESs
sheAdslAturIntervalESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds in the interval. The errored second parameter is a count of one-second intervals containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los or sef defects.

sheAdslAturIntervalSesL.name: sheAdslAturIntervalSesL
sheAdslAturIntervalSesL.description: For the each interval, adslAturIntervalSesL reports the number of seconds during which there have been severely errored seconds-line.

sheAdslAturIntervalUasL.name: sheAdslAturIntervalUasL
sheAdslAturIntervalUasL.description: For the each interval, adslAturIntervalUasL reports the number of seconds during which there have been unavailable seconds-line.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataTable.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataTable
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUR channel.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataEntry.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataEntry
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataEntry.description: An entry in adslAturChanPerfDataTable. This table is only supported by NE releases smaller then R2.5 (NO dualLatency support)!!

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataReceivedBlks.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataReceivedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataReceivedBlks.description: Count of all encoded blocks received on this channel since agent reset.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataTransmittedBlks.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataTransmittedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataTransmittedBlks.description: Count of all encoded blocks transmitted on this channel since agent reset.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCorrectedBlks.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCorrectedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCorrectedBlks.description: Count of all blocks received with errors that were corrected since agent reset. These blocks are passed on as good data.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataUncorrectBlks.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataUncorrectBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataUncorrectBlks.description: Count of all blocks received with uncorrectable errors since agent reset.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnNcd.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnNcd
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnNcd.description: Number of packets with no cell delineation(NCD) error on this channel.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnHec.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnHec
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnHec.description: Number of packets with Header error check (HEC) error on this channel.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPerfValidInterval.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPerfValidIntervals
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPerfValidInterval.description: The number of previous 15-minute intervals in the interval table for which data was collected. Given that <n> is the maximum # of intervals supported. The value will be <n> unless the measurement was (re-)started within the last (<n>*15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals for which the agent has at least some data. In certain cases (e.g., in the case where the agent is a proxy) it is possible that some intervals are unavailable. In this case, this interval is the maximum interval number for which data is available.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPerfInvalidInterv.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPerfInvalidIntervals
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPerfInvalidInterv.description: The number of intervals in the range from 0 to the value of adslAturChanPerfValidIntervals for which no data is available. This object will typically be zero except in cases where the data for some intervals are not available (e.g., in proxy situations).

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElap.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElapsed
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinTimeElap.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval. A full interval is 900 seconds.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinReceived.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinReceivedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinReceived.description: Count of all encoded blocks received on this channel within the current 15 minute interval.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinTransmit.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinTransmittedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinTransmit.description: Count of all encoded blocks transmitted on this channel within the current 15 minute interval.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinCorrecte.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinCorrectedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinCorrecte.description: Count of all blocks received with errors that were corrected on this channel within the current 15 minute interval.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinUncorrec.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinUncorrectBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr15MinUncorrec.description: Count of all blocks received with uncorrectable errors on this channel within the current 15 minute interval.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinNcd.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinNcd
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinNcd.description: Number of packets with no cell delineation(NCD) error on this channel within the current 15 minute time interval.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinHec.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinHec
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinHec.description: Number of packets with Header error check (HEC) error on this channel within the current 15 minute time interval.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElaps.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElapsed
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayTimeElaps.description: Number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the current 1-day interval.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayReceivedB.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayReceivedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayReceivedB.description: Count of all encoded blocks received on this channel during the current day as measured by adslAturChanPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayTransmitt.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayTransmittedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayTransmitt.description: Count of all encoded blocks transmitted on this channel during the current day as measured by adslAturChanPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayCorrected.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayCorrectedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayCorrected.description: Count of all blocks received with errors that were corrected on this channel during the current day as measured by adslAturChanPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayUncorrect.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayUncorrectBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataCurr1DayUncorrect.description: Count of all blocks received with uncorrectable errors on this channel during the current day as measured by adslAturChanPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayNcd.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayNcd
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayNcd.description: Number of packets with no cell delineation (NCD) error on this channel within the current 1 day time interval.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayHec.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayHec
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayHec.description: Number of packets with Header error check (HEC) error on this channel within the current 1 day time interval.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayMoniSecs.description: The amount of time in the previous 1-day interval over which the performance monitoring information is actually counted. This value will be the same as the interval duration except in a situation where performance monitoring data could not be collected for any reason.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayReceivedB.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayReceivedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayReceivedB.description: Count of all encoded blocks received on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayTransmitt.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayTransmittedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayTransmitt.description: Count of all encoded blocks transmitted on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayCorrected.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayCorrectedBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayCorrected.description: Count of all blocks received with errors that were corrected on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayUncorrect.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayUncorrectBlks
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataPrev1DayUncorrect.description: Count of all blocks received with uncorrectable errors on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayNcd.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayNcd
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayNcd.description: Number of packets with no cell delineation (NCD) error on this channel within the most recent previous period.

sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayHec.name: sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayHec
sheAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayHec.description: Number of packets with Header error check (HEC) error on this channel within the most recent previous period.

sheAdslAturChanIntervalTable.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalTable
sheAdslAturChanIntervalTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUR channel's performance data collection interval.

sheAdslAturChanIntervalEntry.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalEntry
sheAdslAturChanIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the adslAturIntervalTable. This table is only supported by NE releases smaller then R2.5 (NO dualLatency support)!!

sheAdslAturChanIntervalNumber.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalNumber
sheAdslAturChanIntervalNumber.description: Performance Data Interval number 1 is the the most recent previous interval; interval 96 is 24 hours ago. Intervals 2..96 are optional.

sheAdslAturChanIntervalValidData.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalValidData
sheAdslAturChanIntervalValidData.description: This variable indicates if the data for this interval is valid.

sheAdslAturChanIntervalEndTime.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalEndTime
sheAdslAturChanIntervalEndTime.description: This variable indicates the time of storing this interval.

sheAdslAturChanIntervalReceivedBlks.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalReceivedBlks
sheAdslAturChanIntervalReceivedBlks.description: Count of all encoded blocks received on this channel during this interval.

sheAdslAturChanIntervalTransmittedBlks.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalTransmittedBlks
sheAdslAturChanIntervalTransmittedBlks.description: Count of all encoded blocks transmitted on this channel during this interval.

sheAdslAturChanIntervalCorrectedBlks.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalCorrectedBlks
sheAdslAturChanIntervalCorrectedBlks.description: Count of all blocks received with errors that were corrected on this channel during this interval.

sheAdslAturChanIntervalUncorrectBlks.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalUncorrectBlks
sheAdslAturChanIntervalUncorrectBlks.description: Count of all blocks received with uncorrectable errors on this channel during this interval.

sheAdslAturChanIntervalNcd.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalNcd
sheAdslAturChanIntervalNcd.description: Indicates count of no cell delineation on this channel for this interval.

sheAdslAturChanIntervalHec.name: sheAdslAturChanIntervalHec
sheAdslAturChanIntervalHec.description: Indicates Header error check counter on this channel during this interval.

sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileTable.name: sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileTable
sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileTable.description: This table contains information on the ADSL line configuration. One entry in this table reflects a profile defined by a manager which can be used to configure the modem for a physical line

sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileEntry.name: sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileEntry
sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileEntry.description: Each entry consists of a list of parameters that represents the configuration of an ADSL modem. 'Dynamic' profiles are implemented. A default profile will always exist. This profile's name will be set to `DEFVAL' and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileName.name: sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileName
sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileName.description: This object is used by the line alarm configuration table in order to identify a row of this table. Dynamic profiles are implemented. The profile name is user specified. The system will always provide a default profile whose name is `DEFVAL'. This characters are not allowed: space : ? leading numbers

sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshFas.name: sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshFastRateUp
sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshFas.description: Applies to `Fast' channels only. Configured change in rate causing an adslAtucRateChangeTrap. A trap is produced when: ChanCurrTxRate >= ChanPrevTxRate plus the value of this object. A value of `0' will disable the trap.

sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshInt.name: sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshInterleaveRateUp
sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshInt.description: Applies to `Interleave' channels only. Configured change in rate causing an adslAtucRateChangeTrap. A trap is produced when: ChanCurrTxRate >= ChanPrevTxRate plus the value of this object. A value of `0' will disable the trap.

sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshFas.name: sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshFastRateDown
sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshFas.description: Applies to `Fast' channels only. Configured change in rate causing an adslAtucRateChangeTrap. A trap is produced when: ChanCurrTxRate <= ChanPrevTxRate minus the value of this object. A value of `0' will disable the trap.

sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshInt.name: sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshInterleaveRateDown
sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThreshInt.description: Applies to `Interleave' channels only. Configured change in rate causing an adslAtucRateChangeTrap. A trap is produced when:ChanCurrTxRate <= ChanPrevTxRate minus the value of this object. A value of `0' will disable the trap.

sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucInitFailu.name: sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucInitFailureTrapEnable
sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucInitFailu.description: Enables and disables the InitFailureTrap. This object is defaulted disable(2).

sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThresh15M.name: sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThresh15MinLofs
sheAdslLineAlarmConfProfileAtucThresh15M.description: The number of Loss of Frame Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface within any given 15 minutes performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an adslAtucPerfLofsThreshTrap. One trap will be sent per interval per interface. A value of `0' will disable the trap.

sheAdslVccTpUsedDslChannel.name: sheAdslVccTpUsedDslChannel
sheAdslVccTpUsedDslChannel.description: This attribute defines the usage of a dsl bearer channel by this VccTp. The availability of dsl channels depends on the configuration of the underlaying adsl line (VccTpSublayerIndex points to this line). Valid values for configuration: fastOnly(2) - only in dualLatency mode available interleavedOnly(3) - only in dualLatency mode available If singleLatency mode is used on the underlaying dslInterface, the port will select the available channel for all existing VccTP's automaticaly. Note: Depending on the used AdslLineProfile configuration, the following scenarios are possible: 1. default state: ->line uses interleaved channel only ->VccTp's uses always the available channel. ->A modification of sheAdslVccTpUsedDslChannel will be rejected! 2. modify line profile ->line uses fast channel only ->VccTp's uses always the available channel. ->CXU send notifications. ->A modification of sheAdslVccTpUsedDslChannel will be rejected! 3. modify line profile ->line uses dualLatency ->VccTp's uses the same channel as before. 4. modify VccTp entry ->line uses dualLatency ->the slected VccTp uses fast or interleaved channel only according to the configuration. ->A setting of value fastOrInterleaved(4) will be rejected. 5. modify line profile ->line goes back to use interleaved channel only ->VccTp's uses the interleaved channel ->notification will be send if a change is needed.

sheAdslAtucPsdRefMaskAdsl2AnnexA.name: sheAdslAtucPsdRefMaskAdsl2AnnexA
sheAdslAtucPsdRefMaskAdsl2AnnexA.description: < PSD reference mask data format description > PSD mask can be described with a set of breakpoints. Breakpoint is a pair of tone index and PSD level. Number of maximum breakpoint is 32. All variable in this format is network byte order (big endian). < Data field of PSD reference mask > Breakpoint# tone index : tone index for breakpoint. Valid range is 1~255 for sheAdslAtucPsdRefMaskAdsl2AnnexA, sheAdslAtucPsdRefMaskAdsl2AnnexB and sheAdslAtucPsdRefMaskAnnexL, 1-511 for sheAdslAtucPsdRefMaskAdsl2plusAnnexA and sheAdslAtucPsdRefMaskAdsl2plusAnnexB. Breakpoint# PSD level : According to ITU-T G.997.1, the PSD maks level shall be coded as an unsigned integer represening PSD levels 0dBm/Hz (coded as 0) to -127.5 dBm/Hz (coded as 255), in the steps of 0.5dBm/Hz, with valid range 0 to -95dBm/Hz. So Valid value range is 0~190. Tone index of first breakpoint should be 1. Tone index of last valid breakpoint should be 255 in case of Adsl2AnnexA, Adsl2AnnexB, AnnexL. And should be 511 for Adsl2plusAnnexA, Adsl2plusAnnexB case Breakpoint should be alligned with increasing tone order. < PSD Reference mask data format (Maximum 128 bytes) > Breakpoint1 tone index (2bytes) Breakpoint1 PSD level (1bytes) Breakpoint2 tone index (2bytes) Breakpoint2 PSD level (1bytes) Breakpoint3 tone index (2bytes) Breakpoint3 PSD level (1bytes) Breakpoint32 tone index (2bytes) Breakpoint32 PSD level (1bytes)

Interleave delay applies only to the interleave channel and defines the mapping (relative spacing) between subsequent input bytes at the interleaver input and their placement in the bit stream at the interleaver output. Larger numbers provide greater separation between consecutive input bytes in the output bit stream allowing for improved impulse noise immunity at the expense of payload latency. In the case where the ifType is Fast(125), use noSuchObject.

sheAdslLineDpboProfileTable.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileTable
sheAdslLineDpboProfileTable.description: The Dpbo Profile Table. Support with SHE R2.6 RP2.

sheAdslLineDpboProfileEntry.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileEntry
sheAdslLineDpboProfileEntry.description: This table contains DPBO profile configuration. For more details, refer ITU-T G.997.1 chapter 7.3.1.2.13.

sheAdslLineDpboProfileIndex.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileIndex
sheAdslLineDpboProfileIndex.description: Table Index, automatically generated when the table entry is created.

sheAdslLineDpboProfileName.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileName
sheAdslLineDpboProfileName.description: This object is used by the line configuration table in order to identify a row of this table for Dpbo profile assign. Special characters are not allowed, like: space : ?

sheAdslLineDpboProfileEsel.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileEsel
sheAdslLineDpboProfileEsel.description: This configuration parameter defines the assumed electrical length of cables (E-side cables) connecting exchange based DSL services to a remote flexibility point (cabinet), that may also host remotely located DSL that is subject to spectrally shaped downstream power backoff depending on this length. For this parameter the electrical length is defined as the loss (in dB) of an equivalent length of hypothetical cable at a reference frequency defined by the network operator or in spectrum management regulations. All values which can be represented by the format are valid values. If this value is zero, the DPBO in this section shall be disabled. If this value is not zero and sheAdslLineDpboProfileEselMin is not 512 (disabled EselMin), sheAdslLineDpboProfileEsel >= sheAdslLineDpboProfileEselMin is required!

sheAdslLineDpboProfileEselMin.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileEselMin
sheAdslLineDpboProfileEselMin.description: This configuration parameter defines the minimum assumed electrical length of cables (E-side cables) connecting exchange based DSL services to a remote flexibility point (cabinet), that may also host remotely located DSL that is subject to spectrally shaped downstream power backoff depending on this length. For this parameter the electrical length is defined as the loss (in dB) of an equivalent length of hypothetical cable at a reference frequency defined by the network operator or in spectrum management regulations. All values which can be represented by the format are valid values. Default: sheAdslLineDpboProfileEselMin = 512 If this value is not 512 (disabled) and sheAdslLineDpboProfileEsel is not zero (DPBO disabled), sheAdslLineDpboProfileEsel >= sheAdslLineDpboProfileEselMin is required!

sheAdslLineDpboProfileMus.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileMus
sheAdslLineDpboProfileMus.description: DPBOMUS defines the assumed Minimum Usable receive Signal PSD (in dBm/Hz) for exchange based services, used to modify parameter DPBOFMAX defined below. All values which can be represented by the format are valid values: 0 = 0 dBm/Hz .. -127.5 dBm/Hz (coded as 255).

sheAdslLineDpboProfileMof.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileMof
sheAdslLineDpboProfileMof.description: DPBOMOF (mask overall floor) defines the absolut minimum of the used PSD mask (in dBm/Hz) for exchange based services. All values which can be represented by the format are valid values: 0 = 0 dBm/Hz .. -127.5 dBm/Hz (coded as 255). Note: Not longer supported!

sheAdslLineDpboProfileFMin.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileFMin
sheAdslLineDpboProfileFMin.description: DPBO shall be applied in the range starting at DPBOFMIN and should be configured as an subcarrier index. The range of valid values is from 1 to 512.

sheAdslLineDpboProfileFMax.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileFMax
sheAdslLineDpboProfileFMax.description: The maximum subcarrier at which DPBO may be applied is DPBOFMAX. The range of valid values is from 1 to 512.

sheAdslLineDpboProfileEpsd.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileEpsd
sheAdslLineDpboProfileEpsd.description: Used PSD mask that is assumed to be permitted at the exchange. The set of breakpoints can be represented as [(t1, PSD1),(t2, PSD2), .. , (tN, PSDN)]. The subcarrier index (tN) shall be coded as an unsigned integer (16 bit, range 1..512). The MIB PSD mask level (PSDN) shall be coded as an unsigned integer (16 bit) representing the MIB PSD mask levels 0 dBm/Hz (coded as 0) to -127.5 dBm/Hz (coded as 255), in steps of 0.5 dBm/Hz. The maximum number of breakpoints for DPBOEPSD is 16. If less then maximum breakpoints will be defined, all used breakpoints should be configured in a consecutive way without spaces (t1 - t2 - t3.. and not t1 - t5 - t7..). The default value should be set according PSD settings for ADSL2+. Subcarrier PSD 59 -36.5 256 -36.5 314 -42 376 -46.5 499 -47.5

sheAdslLineDpboProfileEScmA.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileEScmA
sheAdslLineDpboProfileEScmA.description: This configuration parameter defines a cable model in terms of three scalars DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB and DPBOESCMC that are used to estimate the frequency dependent loss of E-side cables calculated from the DPBOESEL parameter using the formula: ESCM(f) = (DPBOESCMA + DPBOESCMB*sqrt(f) + DPBOESCMC*f )*DPBOESCL Where ESCM is expressed in dB and f is expressed in MHz. DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB, DPBOESCMC shall be coded as unsigned integers representing a scalar value from -1 (coded as 0) to 1.5 (coded as 640) in step of 2^-8. All values are valid.

sheAdslLineDpboProfileEScmB.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileEScmB
sheAdslLineDpboProfileEScmB.description: This configuration parameter defines a cable model in terms of three scalars DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB and DPBOESCMC that are used to estimate the frequency dependent loss of E-side cables calculated from the DPBOESEL parameter using the formula: ESCM(f) = (DPBOESCMA + DPBOESCMB*sqrt(f) + DPBOESCMC*f )*DPBOESCL Where ESCM is expressed in dB and f is expressed in MHz. DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB, DPBOESCMC shall be coded as unsigned integers representing a scalar value from -1 (coded as 0) to 1.5 (coded as 640) in step of 2^-8. All values are valid.

sheAdslLineDpboProfileEScmC.name: sheAdslLineDpboProfileEScmC
sheAdslLineDpboProfileEScmC.description: This configuration parameter defines a cable model in terms of three scalars DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB and DPBOESCMC that are used to estimate the frequency dependent loss of E-side cables calculated from the DPBOESEL parameter using the formula: ESCM(f) = (DPBOESCMA + DPBOESCMB*sqrt(f) + DPBOESCMC*f )*DPBOESCL Where ESCM is expressed in dB and f is expressed in MHz. DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB, DPBOESCMC shall be coded as unsigned integers representing a scalar value from -1 (coded as 0) to 1.5 (coded as 640) in step of 2^-8. All values are valid.
